var book = {
	"name": "2 Chronicles",
	"numChapters": 36,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11196A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11196A\"></sup>Solomon the son of David established himself securely over his kingdom, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God <i>was</i> with him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11196B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11196B\"></sup>exalted him greatly.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Solomon spoke to all Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11197C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11197C\"></sup>to the commanders of thousands and of hundreds and to the judges and to every leader in all Israel, the heads of the fathers’ <i>households</i>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then Solomon and all the assembly with him went to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11198D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11198D\"></sup>the high place which was at Gibeon, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11198E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11198E\"></sup>for God’s tent of meeting was there, which Moses the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had made in the wilderness.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>However, David had brought up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11199F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11199F\"></sup>the ark of God from Kiriath-jearim to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11199G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11199G\"></sup>the place he had prepared for it, for he had pitched a tent for it in Jerusalem.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11200H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11200H\"></sup>the bronze altar, which Bezalel the son of Uri, the son of Hur, had made, was there before the tabernacle of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and Solomon and the assembly sought it out.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Solomon went up there before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to the bronze altar which <i>was</i> at the tent of meeting, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11201I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11201I\"></sup>offered a thousand burnt offerings on it.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11202J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11202J\"></sup>In that night God appeared to Solomon and said to him, “Ask what I shall give you.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Solomon said to God, “You have dealt with my father David with great lovingkindness, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11203K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11203K\"></sup>have made me king in his place.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11204L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11204L\"></sup>Your promise to my father David is fulfilled, for You have made me king over <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11204M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11204M\"></sup>a people as numerous as the dust of the earth.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11205N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11205N\"></sup>Give me now wisdom and knowledge, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11205O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11205O\"></sup>that I may go out and come in before this people, for who can rule this great people of Yours?”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11206P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11206P\"></sup>God said to Solomon, “Because you had this in mind, and did not ask for riches, wealth or honor, or the life of those who hate you, nor have you even asked for long life, but you have asked for yourself wisdom and knowledge that you may rule My people over whom I have made you king,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>wisdom and knowledge have been granted to you. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11207Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11207Q\"></sup>I will give you riches and wealth and honor, such as none of the kings who were before you has possessed nor those who will come after you.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11208R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11208R\"></sup>So Solomon went from the high place which was at Gibeon, from the tent of meeting, to Jerusalem, and he reigned over Israel.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11209S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11209S\"></sup>Solomon amassed chariots and horsemen. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11209T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11209T\"></sup>He had 1,400 chariots and 12,000 horsemen, and he stationed them in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11209U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11209U\"></sup>the chariot cities and with the king at Jerusalem.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11210V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11210V\"></sup>The king made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11210W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11210W\"></sup>silver and gold as plentiful in Jerusalem as stones, and he made cedars as plentiful as sycamores in the lowland.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Solomon’s <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11211X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11211X\"></sup>horses were imported from Egypt and from Kue; the king’s traders procured them from Kue for a price.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>They imported chariots from Egypt for 600 <i>shekels</i> of silver apiece and horses for 150 apiece, and by the same means they exported them to all the kings of the Hittites and the kings of Aram."
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11213A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11213A\"></sup>Now Solomon decided to build a house for the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and a royal palace for himself.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11214B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11214B\"></sup>Solomon assigned 70,000 men to carry loads and 80,000 men to quarry <i>stone</i> in the mountains and 3,600 to supervise them.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11215C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11215C\"></sup>Then Solomon sent <i>word</i> to Huram the king of Tyre, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11215D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11215D\"></sup>As you dealt with David my father and sent him cedars to build him a house to dwell in, so do for me.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Behold, I am about to build a house for the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God, dedicating it to Him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11216E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11216E\"></sup>to burn fragrant incense before Him and <i>to set out</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11216F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11216F\"></sup>the showbread continually, and to offer <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11216G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11216G\"></sup>burnt offerings morning and evening, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11216H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11216H\"></sup>on sabbaths and on new moons and on the appointed feasts of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, this <i>being required</i> forever in Israel.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The house which I am about to build <i>will be</i> great, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11217I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11217I\"></sup>greater is our God than all the gods.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11218J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11218J\"></sup>who is able to build a house for Him, for the heavens and the highest heavens cannot contain Him? So who am I, that I should build a house for Him, except to burn <i>incense</i> before Him?",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11219K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11219K\"></sup>send me a skilled man to work in gold, silver, brass and iron, and in purple, crimson and violet <i>fabrics</i>, and who knows how to make engravings, to <i>work</i> with the skilled men <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11219L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11219L\"></sup>whom I have in Judah and Jerusalem, whom David my father provided.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11220M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11220M\"></sup>Send me also cedar, cypress and algum timber from Lebanon, for I know that your servants know how to cut timber of Lebanon; and indeed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11220N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11220N\"></sup>my servants <i>will work</i> with your servants,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>to prepare timber in abundance for me, for the house which I am about to build <i>will be</i> great and wonderful.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11222O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11222O\"></sup>I will give to your servants, the woodsmen who cut the timber, 20,000 kors of crushed wheat and 20,000 kors of barley, and 20,000 baths of wine and 20,000 baths of oil.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then Huram, king of Tyre, answered in a letter sent to Solomon: “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11223P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11223P\"></sup>Because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> loves His people, He has made you king over them.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then Huram continued, “Blessed be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11224Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11224Q\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, who has made heaven and earth, who has given King David a wise son, endowed with discretion and understanding, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11224R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11224R\"></sup>who will build a house for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and a royal palace for himself.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“Now I am sending Huram-abi, a skilled man, endowed with understanding,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11226S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11226S\"></sup>the son of a Danite woman and a Tyrian father, who knows how to work in gold, silver, bronze, iron, stone and wood, <i>and</i> in purple, violet, linen and crimson fabrics, and <i>who knows how</i> to make all kinds of engravings and to execute any design which may be assigned to him, <i>to work</i> with your skilled men and with those of my lord David your father.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now then, let my lord send to his servants wheat and barley, oil and wine, of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11227T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11227T\"></sup>which he has spoken.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11228U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11228U\"></sup>We will cut whatever timber you need from Lebanon and bring it to you on rafts by sea to Joppa, so that you may carry it up to Jerusalem.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Solomon numbered all the aliens who <i>were</i> in the land of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11229V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11229V\"></sup>following the census which his father David had taken; and 153,600 were found.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11230W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11230W\"></sup>He appointed 70,000 of them to carry loads and 80,000 to quarry <i>stones</i> in the mountains and 3,600 supervisors to make the people work."
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11231A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11231A\"></sup>Then Solomon began to build the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in Jerusalem on Mount Moriah, where <i>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span></i> had appeared to his father David, at the place that David had prepared <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11231B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11231B\"></sup>on the threshing floor of Ornan the Jebusite.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He began to build on the second <i>day</i> in the second month of the fourth year of his reign.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now these are the foundations which <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11233C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11233C\"></sup>Solomon laid for building the house of God. The length in cubits, according to the old standard <i>was</i> sixty cubits, and the width twenty cubits.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The porch which was in front of the house <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11234D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11234D\"></sup>was as long as the width of the house, twenty cubits, and the height 120; and inside he overlaid it with pure gold.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He overlaid <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11235E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11235E\"></sup>the main room with cypress wood and overlaid it with fine gold, and ornamented it with palm trees and chains.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Further, he adorned the house with precious stones; and the gold was gold from Parvaim.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11237F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11237F\"></sup>He also overlaid the house with gold—the beams, the thresholds and its walls and its doors; and he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11237G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11237G\"></sup>carved cherubim on the walls.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now he made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11238H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11238H\"></sup>the room of the holy of holies: its length across the width of the house <i>was</i> twenty cubits, and its width <i>was</i> twenty cubits; and he overlaid it with fine gold, <i>amounting</i> to 600 talents.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The weight of the nails was fifty shekels of gold. He also overlaid <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11239I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11239I\"></sup>the upper rooms with gold.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11240J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11240J\"></sup>Then he made two sculptured cherubim in the room of the holy of holies and overlaid them with gold.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The wingspan of the cherubim <i>was</i> twenty cubits; the wing of one, of five cubits, touched the wall of the house, and <i>its</i> other wing, of five cubits, touched the wing of the other cherub.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The wing of the other cherub, of five cubits, touched the wall of the house; and <i>its</i> other wing of five cubits was attached to the wing of the first cherub.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The wings of these cherubim extended twenty cubits, and they stood on their feet facing the <i>main</i> room.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11244K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11244K\"></sup>He made the veil of violet, purple, crimson and fine linen, and he worked cherubim on it.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11245L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11245L\"></sup>He also made two pillars for the front of the house, thirty-five cubits high, and the capital on the top of each <i>was</i> five cubits.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He made chains in the inner sanctuary and placed <i>them</i> on the tops of the pillars; and he made one hundred pomegranates and placed <i>them</i> on the chains.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11247M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11247M\"></sup>He erected the pillars in front of the temple, one on the right and the other on the left, and named the one on the right Jachin and the one on the left Boaz."
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11248A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11248A\"></sup>he made a bronze altar, twenty cubits in length and twenty cubits in width and ten cubits in height.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11249B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11249B\"></sup>Also he made the cast <i>metal</i> sea, ten cubits from brim to brim, circular in form, and its height <i>was</i> five cubits and its circumference thirty cubits.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now figures like oxen <i>were</i> under it <i>and</i> all around it, ten cubits, entirely encircling the sea. The oxen <i>were</i> in two rows, cast in one piece.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>It stood on twelve oxen, three facing the north, three facing west, three facing south and three facing east; and the sea <i>was set</i> on top of them and all their hindquarters turned inwards.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>It was a handbreadth thick, and its brim was made like the brim of a cup, <i>like</i> a lily blossom; it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11252C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11252C\"></sup>could hold 3,000 baths.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11253D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11253D\"></sup>He also made ten basins in which to wash, and he set five on the right side and five on the left to rinse things for the burnt offering; but the sea <i>was</i> for the priests to wash in.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11254E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11254E\"></sup>he made the ten golden lampstands in the way prescribed for them and he set them in the temple, five on the right side and five on the left.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He also made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11255F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11255F\"></sup>ten tables and placed them in the temple, five on the right side and five on the left. And he made one hundred golden bowls.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then he made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11256G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11256G\"></sup>the court of the priests and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11256H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11256H\"></sup>the great court and doors for the court, and overlaid their doors with bronze.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11257I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11257I\"></sup>He set the sea on the right side <i>of the house</i> toward the southeast.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11258J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11258J\"></sup>Huram also made the pails, the shovels and the bowls. So Huram finished doing the work which he performed for King Solomon in the house of God:",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>the two pillars, the bowls and the two capitals on top of the pillars, and the two networks to cover the two bowls of the capitals which were on top of the pillars,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11260K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11260K\"></sup>the four hundred pomegranates for the two networks, two rows of pomegranates for each network to cover the two bowls of the capitals which were on the pillars.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11261L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11261L\"></sup>He also made the stands and he made the basins on the stands,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><i>and</i> the one sea with the twelve oxen under it.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The pails, the shovels, the forks and all its utensils, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11263M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11263M\"></sup>Huram-abi made of polished bronze for King Solomon for the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>On the plain of the Jordan the king cast them in the clay ground between Succoth and Zeredah.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11265N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11265N\"></sup>Thus Solomon made all these utensils in great quantities, for the weight of the bronze could not be found out.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Solomon also made all the things that <i>were</i> in the house of God: even the golden altar, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11266O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11266O\"></sup>the tables with the bread of the Presence on them,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>the lampstands with their lamps of pure gold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11267P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11267P\"></sup>to burn in front of the inner sanctuary in the way prescribed;",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>the flowers, the lamps, and the tongs of gold, of purest gold;",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>and the snuffers, the bowls, the spoons and the firepans of pure gold; and the entrance of the house, its inner doors for the holy of holies and the doors of the house, <i>that is</i>, of the nave, of gold."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11270A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11270A\"></sup>Thus all the work that Solomon performed for the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was finished. And Solomon brought in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11270B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11270B\"></sup>things that David his father had dedicated, even the silver and the gold and all the utensils, <i>and</i> put <i>them</i> in the treasuries of the house of God.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11271C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11271C\"></sup>Then Solomon assembled to Jerusalem the elders of Israel and all the heads of the tribes, the leaders of the fathers’ <i>households</i> of the sons of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11271D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11271D\"></sup>to bring up the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> out of the city of David, which is Zion.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11272E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11272E\"></sup>All the men of Israel assembled themselves to the king at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11272F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11272F\"></sup>the feast, that is <i>in</i> the seventh month.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then all the elders of Israel came, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11273G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11273G\"></sup>the Levites took up the ark.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They brought up the ark and the tent of meeting and all the holy utensils which <i>were</i> in the tent; the Levitical priests brought them up.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And King Solomon and all the congregation of Israel who were assembled with him before the ark, were sacrificing so many sheep and oxen that they could not be counted or numbered.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then the priests brought the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to its place, into the inner sanctuary of the house, to the holy of holies, under the wings of the cherubim.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>For the cherubim spread their wings over the place of the ark, so that the cherubim made a covering over the ark and its poles.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The poles were so long that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11278H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11278H\"></sup>the ends of the poles of the ark could be seen in front of the inner sanctuary, but they could not be seen outside; and they are there to this day.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11279I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11279I\"></sup>There was nothing in the ark except the two tablets which Moses put <i>there</i> at Horeb, where the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> made a covenant with the sons of Israel, when they came out of Egypt.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When the priests came forth from the holy place (for all the priests who were present had sanctified themselves, without regard <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11280J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11280J\"></sup>to divisions),",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>and all the Levitical singers, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11281K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11281K\"></sup>Asaph, Heman, Jeduthun, and their sons and kinsmen, clothed in fine linen, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11281L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11281L\"></sup>with cymbals, harps and lyres, standing east of the altar, and with them one hundred and twenty priests <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11281M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11281M\"></sup>blowing trumpets",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>in unison when the trumpeters and the singers were to make themselves heard with one voice to praise and to glorify the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and when they lifted up their voice <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11282N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11282N\"></sup>accompanied by trumpets and cymbals and instruments of music, and when they praised the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <i>saying</i>, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11282O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11282O\"></sup><i>He</i> indeed is good for His lovingkindness is everlasting,” then the house, the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, was filled with a cloud,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>so that the priests could not stand to minister because of the cloud, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11283P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11283P\"></sup>the glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> filled the house of God."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11284A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11284A\"></sup>Then Solomon said,“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has said that He would dwell in the thick cloud.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“I have built You a lofty house,And a place for Your dwelling forever.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then the king faced about and blessed all the assembly of Israel, while all the assembly of Israel was standing.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He said, “Blessed be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, who spoke with His mouth to my father David and has fulfilled <i>it</i> with His hands, saying,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>‘Since the day that I brought My people from the land of Egypt, I did not choose a city out of all the tribes of Israel <i>in which</i> to build a house that My name might be there, nor did I choose any man for a leader over My people Israel;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11289B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11289B\"></sup>I have chosen Jerusalem that My name might be there, and I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11289C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11289C\"></sup>have chosen David to be over My people Israel.’",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11290D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11290D\"></sup>Now it was in the heart of my father David to build a house for the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to my father David, ‘Because it was in your heart to build a house for My name, you did well that it was in your heart.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Nevertheless you shall not build the house, but your son who will be born to you, he shall build the house for My name.’",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has fulfilled His word which He spoke; for I have risen in the place of my father David and sit on the throne of Israel, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> promised, and have built the house for the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>There I have set the ark <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11294E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11294E\"></sup>in which is the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which He made with the sons of Israel.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then he stood before the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in the presence of all the assembly of Israel and spread out his hands.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11296F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11296F\"></sup>Now Solomon had made a bronze platform, five cubits long, five cubits wide and three cubits high, and had set it in the midst of the court; and he stood on it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11296G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11296G\"></sup>knelt on his knees in the presence of all the assembly of Israel and spread out his hands toward heaven.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He said, “O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11297H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11297H\"></sup>there is no god like You in heaven or on earth, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11297I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11297I\"></sup>keeping covenant and <i>showing</i> lovingkindness to Your servants who walk before You with all their heart;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11298J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11298J\"></sup>who has kept with Your servant David, my father, that which You have promised him; indeed You have spoken with Your mouth and have fulfilled it with Your hand, as it is this day.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Now therefore, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, keep with Your servant David, my father, that which You have promised him, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11299K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11299K\"></sup>You shall not lack a man to sit on the throne of Israel, if only your sons take heed to their way, to walk in My law as you have walked before Me.’",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Now therefore, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, let Your word be confirmed which You have spoken to Your servant David.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11301L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11301L\"></sup>will God indeed dwell with mankind on the earth? Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11301M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11301M\"></sup>heaven and the highest heaven cannot contain You; how much less this house which I have built.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Yet have regard to the prayer of Your servant and to his supplication, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God, to listen to the cry and to the prayer which Your servant prays before You;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>that Your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11303N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11303N\"></sup>eye may be open toward this house day and night, toward <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11303O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11303O\"></sup>the place of which You have said that <i>You would</i> put Your name there, to listen to the prayer which Your servant shall pray toward this place.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Listen to the supplications of Your servant and of Your people Israel when they pray toward this place; hear from Your dwelling place, from heaven; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11304P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11304P\"></sup>hear and forgive.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“If a man sins against his neighbor and is made to take an oath, and he comes <i>and</i> takes an oath before Your altar in this house,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>then hear from heaven and act and judge Your servants, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11306Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11306Q\"></sup>punishing the wicked by bringing his way on his own head and justifying the righteous by giving him according to his righteousness.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“If Your people Israel are defeated before an enemy because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11307R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11307R\"></sup>they have sinned against You, and they return <i>to You</i> and confess Your name, and pray and make supplication before You in this house,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>then hear from heaven and forgive the sin of Your people Israel, and bring them back to the land which You have given to them and to their fathers.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“When the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11309S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11309S\"></sup>heavens are shut up and there is no rain because they have sinned against You, and they pray toward this place and confess Your name, and turn from their sin when You afflict them;",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>then hear in heaven and forgive the sin of Your servants and Your people Israel, indeed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11310T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11310T\"></sup>teach them the good way in which they should walk. And send rain on Your land which You have given to Your people for an inheritance.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“If there is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11311U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11311U\"></sup>famine in the land, if there is pestilence, if there is blight or mildew, if there is locust or grasshopper, if their enemies besiege them in the land of their cities, whatever plague or whatever sickness <i>there is</i>,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>whatever prayer or supplication is made by any man or by all Your people Israel, each knowing his own affliction and his own pain, and spreading his hands toward this house,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>then hear from heaven Your dwelling place, and forgive, and render to each according to all his ways, whose heart You know <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11313V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11313V\"></sup>for You alone know the hearts of the sons of men,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>that they may fear You, to walk in Your ways as long as they live in the land which You have given to our fathers.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>“Also concerning <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11315W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11315W\"></sup>the foreigner who is not from Your people Israel, when he comes from a far country for Your great name’s sake and Your mighty hand and Your outstretched arm, when they come and pray toward this house,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>then hear from heaven, from Your dwelling place, and do according to all for which the foreigner calls to You, in order that all the peoples of the earth may know Your name, and fear You as <i>do</i> Your people Israel, and that they may know that this house which I have built is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11316X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11316X\"></sup>called by Your name.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“When Your people go out to battle against their enemies, by whatever way You shall send them, and they pray to You toward this city which You have chosen and the house which I have built for Your name,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>then hear from heaven their prayer and their supplication, and maintain their cause.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>“When they sin against You (<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11319Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11319Y\"></sup>for there is no man who does not sin) and You are angry with them and deliver them to an enemy, so that they take them away captive to a land far off or near,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>if they take thought in the land where they are taken captive, and repent and make supplication to You in the land of their captivity, saying, ‘We have sinned, we have committed iniquity and have acted wickedly’;",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11321Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11321Z\"></sup>if they return to You with all their heart and with all their soul in the land of their captivity, where they have been taken captive, and pray toward their land which You have given to their fathers and the city which You have chosen, and toward the house which I have built for Your name,",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>then hear from heaven, from Your dwelling place, their prayer and supplications, and maintain their cause and forgive Your people who have sinned against You.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>“Now, O my God, I pray, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11323AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11323AA\"></sup>let Your eyes be open and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11323AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11323AB\"></sup>Your ears attentive to the prayer <i>offered</i> in this place.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11324AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11324AC\"></sup>Now therefore arise, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God, to Your resting place, You and the ark of Your might; let Your priests, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God, be clothed with salvation and let Your godly ones rejoice in what is good.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>“O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God, do not turn away the face of Your anointed; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11325AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11325AD\"></sup>remember <i>Your</i> lovingkindness to Your servant David.”"
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11326A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11326A\"></sup>Now when Solomon had finished praying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11326B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11326B\"></sup>fire came down from heaven and consumed the burnt offering and the sacrifices, and the glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> filled the house.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11327C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11327C\"></sup>The priests could not enter into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> because the glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> filled the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> house.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>All the sons of Israel, seeing the fire come down and the glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> upon the house, bowed down on the pavement with their faces to the ground, and they worshiped and gave praise to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <i>saying</i>, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11328D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11328D\"></sup>Truly He is good, truly His lovingkindness is everlasting.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11329E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11329E\"></sup>Then the king and all the people offered sacrifice before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>King Solomon offered a sacrifice of 22,000 oxen and 120,000 sheep. Thus the king and all the people dedicated the house of God.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The priests stood at their posts, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11331F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11331F\"></sup>the Levites also, with the instruments of music to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which King David had made for giving praise to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>—“for His lovingkindness is everlasting”—whenever he gave praise by their means, while <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11331G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11331G\"></sup>the priests on the other side blew trumpets; and all Israel was standing.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11332H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11332H\"></sup>Then Solomon consecrated the middle of the court that <i>was</i> before the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for there he offered the burnt offerings and the fat of the peace offerings because the bronze altar which Solomon had made was not able to contain the burnt offering, the grain offering and the fat.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11333I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11333I\"></sup>Solomon observed the feast at that time for seven days, and all Israel with him, a very great assembly <i>who came</i> from the entrance of Hamath to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11333J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11333J\"></sup>brook of Egypt.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>On the eighth day they held <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11334K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11334K\"></sup>a solemn assembly, for the dedication of the altar they observed seven days and the feast seven days.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then on the twenty-third day of the seventh month he sent the people to their tents, rejoicing and happy of heart because of the goodness that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had shown to David and to Solomon and to His people Israel.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11336L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11336L\"></sup>Thus Solomon finished the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the king’s palace, and successfully completed all that he had planned on doing in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and in his palace.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared to Solomon at night and said to him, “I have heard your prayer and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11337M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11337M\"></sup>have chosen this place for Myself as a house of sacrifice.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11338N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11338N\"></sup>If I shut up the heavens so that there is no rain, or if I command the locust to devour the land, or if I send pestilence among My people,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11339O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11339O\"></sup>and My people who are called by My name humble themselves and pray and seek My face and turn from their wicked ways, then I will hear from heaven, will forgive their sin and will heal their land.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11340P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11340P\"></sup>Now My eyes will be open and My ears attentive to the prayer <i>offered</i> in this place.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11341Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11341Q\"></sup>now I have chosen and consecrated this house that My name may be there forever, and My eyes and My heart will be there perpetually.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>As for you, if you walk before Me as your father David walked, even to do according to all that I have commanded you, and will keep My statutes and My ordinances,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>then I will establish your royal throne as I covenanted with your father David, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11343R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11343R\"></sup>You shall not lack a man <i>to be</i> ruler in Israel.’",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11344S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11344S\"></sup>But if you turn away and forsake My statutes and My commandments which I have set before you, and go and serve other gods and worship them,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11345T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11345T\"></sup>then I will uproot you from My land which I have given you, and this house which I have consecrated for My name I will cast out of My sight and I will make it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11345U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11345U\"></sup>a proverb and a byword among all peoples.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>As for this house, which was exalted, everyone who passes by it will be astonished and say, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11346V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11346V\"></sup>Why has the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> done thus to this land and to this house?’",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And they will say, ‘Because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11347W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11347W\"></sup>they forsook the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their fathers who brought them from the land of Egypt, and they adopted other gods and worshiped them and served them; therefore He has brought all this adversity on them.’”"
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11348A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11348A\"></sup>Now it came about at the end of the twenty years in which Solomon had built the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and his own house",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>that he built the cities which Huram had given to him, and settled the sons of Israel there.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then Solomon went to Hamath-zobah and captured it.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He built Tadmor in the wilderness and all the storage cities which he had built in Hamath.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He also built upper <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11352B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11352B\"></sup>Beth-horon and lower Beth-horon, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11352C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11352C\"></sup>fortified cities <i>with</i> walls, gates and bars;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and Baalath and all the storage cities that Solomon had, and all the cities for his chariots and cities for his horsemen, and all that it pleased Solomon to build in Jerusalem, in Lebanon, and in all the land under his rule.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11354D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11354D\"></sup>All of the people who were left of the Hittites, the Amorites, the Perizzites, the Hivites and the Jebusites, who were not of Israel,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><i>namely</i>, from their descendants who were left after them in the land whom the sons of Israel had not destroyed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11355E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11355E\"></sup>them Solomon raised as forced laborers to this day.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But Solomon did not make slaves for his work from the sons of Israel; they were men of war, his chief captains and commanders of his chariots and his horsemen.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>These were the chief officers of King Solomon, two hundred and fifty who ruled over the people.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11358F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11358F\"></sup>Then Solomon brought Pharaoh’s daughter up from the city of David to the house which he had built for her, for he said, “My wife shall not dwell in the house of David king of Israel, because the places are holy where the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has entered.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then Solomon offered burnt offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11359G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11359G\"></sup>the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> which he had built before the porch;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11360H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11360H\"></sup><i>did so</i> according to the daily rule, offering <i>them</i> up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11360I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11360I\"></sup>according to the commandment of Moses, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11360J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11360J\"></sup>the sabbaths, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11360K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11360K\"></sup>the new moons and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11360L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11360L\"></sup>three annual feasts—the Feast of Unleavened Bread, the Feast of Weeks and the Feast of Booths.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Now according to the ordinance of his father David, he appointed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11361M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11361M\"></sup>the divisions of the priests for their service, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11361N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11361N\"></sup>the Levites for their duties of praise and ministering before the priests according to the daily rule, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11361O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11361O\"></sup>the gatekeepers by their divisions at every gate; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11361P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11361P\"></sup>David the man of God had so commanded.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And they did not depart from the commandment of the king to the priests and Levites in any manner or concerning the storehouses.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Thus all the work of Solomon was carried out from the day of the foundation of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and until it was finished. So the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was completed.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Solomon went to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11364Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11364Q\"></sup>Ezion-geber and to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11364R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11364R\"></sup>Eloth on the seashore in the land of Edom.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And Huram by his servants sent him ships and servants who knew the sea; and they went with Solomon’s servants to Ophir, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11365S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11365S\"></sup>took from there four hundred and fifty talents of gold and brought them to King Solomon."
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11366A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11366A\"></sup>Now when the queen of Sheba heard of the fame of Solomon, she came to Jerusalem to test Solomon with difficult questions. She had a very large retinue, with camels carrying spices and a large amount of gold and precious stones; and when she came to Solomon, she spoke with him about all that was on her heart.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Solomon answered all her questions; nothing was hidden from Solomon which he did not explain to her.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When the queen of Sheba had seen the wisdom of Solomon, the house which he had built,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>the food at his table, the seating of his servants, the attendance of his ministers and their attire, his cupbearers and their attire, and his stairway by which he went up to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, she was breathless.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then she said to the king, “It was a true report which I heard in my own land about your words and your wisdom.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Nevertheless I did not believe their reports until I came and my eyes had seen it. And behold, the half of the greatness of your wisdom was not told me. You surpass the report that I heard.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>How blessed are your men, how blessed are these your servants who stand before you continually and hear your wisdom.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Blessed be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God who delighted in you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11373B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11373B\"></sup>setting you on His throne as king for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11373C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11373C\"></sup>because your God loved Israel establishing them forever, therefore He made you king over them, to do justice and righteousness.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then she gave the king one hundred and twenty talents of gold and a very great <i>amount of</i> spices and precious stones; there had never been spice like that which the queen of Sheba gave to King Solomon.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The servants of Huram and the servants of Solomon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11375D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11375D\"></sup>who brought gold from Ophir, also brought algum trees and precious stones.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>From the algum trees the king made steps for the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and for the king’s palace, and lyres and harps for the singers; and none like that was seen before in the land of Judah.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>King Solomon gave to the queen of Sheba all her desire which she requested besides <i>a return for</i> what she had brought to the king. Then she turned and went to her own land with her servants.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11378E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11378E\"></sup>Now the weight of gold which came to Solomon in one year was 666 talents of gold,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>besides that which the traders and merchants brought; and all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11379F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11379F\"></sup>the kings of Arabia and the governors of the country brought gold and silver to Solomon.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>King Solomon made 200 large shields of beaten gold, using 600 <i>shekels of</i> beaten gold on each large shield.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><i>He made</i> 300 shields of beaten gold, using three hundred shekels of gold on each shield, and the king put them in the house of the forest of Lebanon.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Moreover, the king made a great throne of ivory and overlaid it with pure gold.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><i>There were</i> six steps to the throne and a footstool in gold attached to the throne, and arms on each side of the seat, and two lions standing beside the arms.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Twelve lions were standing there on the six steps on the one side and on the other; nothing like <i>it</i> was made for any <i>other</i> kingdom.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>All King Solomon’s drinking vessels <i>were</i> of gold, and all the vessels of the house of the forest of Lebanon <i>were</i> of pure gold; silver was not considered valuable in the days of Solomon.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11386G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11386G\"></sup>For the king had ships which went to Tarshish with the servants of Huram; once every three years the ships of Tarshish came bringing gold and silver, ivory and apes and peacocks.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11387H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11387H\"></sup>So King Solomon became greater than all the kings of the earth in riches and wisdom.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And all the kings of the earth were seeking the presence of Solomon, to hear his wisdom which God had put in his heart.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11389I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11389I\"></sup>They brought every man his gift, articles of silver and gold, garments, weapons, spices, horses and mules, so much year by year.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Now Solomon had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11390J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11390J\"></sup>4,000 stalls for horses and chariots and 12,000 horsemen, and he stationed them in the chariot cities and with the king in Jerusalem.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11391K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11391K\"></sup>He was the ruler over all the kings from the Euphrates River even to the land of the Philistines, and as far as the border of Egypt.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11392L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11392L\"></sup>The king made silver <i>as common</i> as stones in Jerusalem, and he made cedars as plentiful as sycamore trees that are in the lowland.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11393M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11393M\"></sup>And they were bringing horses for Solomon from Egypt and from all countries.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11394N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11394N\"></sup>Now the rest of the acts of Solomon, from first to last, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11394O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11394O\"></sup>are they not written in the records of Nathan the prophet, and in the prophecy of Ahijah the Shilonite, and in the visions of Iddo the seer concerning Jeroboam the son of Nebat?",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11395P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11395P\"></sup>Solomon reigned forty years in Jerusalem over all Israel.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And Solomon slept with his fathers and was buried in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11396Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11396Q\"></sup>the city of his father David; and his son Rehoboam reigned in his place."
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11397A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11397A\"></sup>Then Rehoboam went to Shechem, for all Israel had come to Shechem to make him king.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>When Jeroboam the son of Nebat heard <i>of it</i> (for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11398B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11398B\"></sup>he was in Egypt where he had fled from the presence of King Solomon), Jeroboam returned from Egypt.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So they sent and summoned him. When Jeroboam and all Israel came, they spoke to Rehoboam, saying,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“Your father made our <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11400C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11400C\"></sup>yoke hard; now therefore lighten the hard service of your father and his heavy yoke which he put on us, and we will serve you.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He said to them, “Return to me again in three days.” So the people departed.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then King Rehoboam <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11402D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11402D\"></sup>consulted with the elders who had served his father Solomon while he was still alive, saying, “How do you counsel <i>me</i> to answer this people?”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They spoke to him, saying, “If you will be kind to this people and please them and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11403E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11403E\"></sup>speak good words to them, then they will be your servants forever.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11404F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11404F\"></sup>forsook the counsel of the elders which they had given him, and consulted with the young men who grew up with him and served him.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So he said to them, “What counsel do you give that we may answer this people, who have spoken to me, saying, ‘Lighten the yoke which your father put on us’?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The young men who grew up with him spoke to him, saying, “Thus you shall say to the people who spoke to you, saying, ‘Your father made our yoke heavy, but you make it lighter for us.’ Thus you shall say to them, ‘My little finger is thicker than my father’s loins!",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Whereas my father loaded you with a heavy yoke, I will add to your yoke; my father disciplined you with whips, but I <i>will discipline you</i> with scorpions.’”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So Jeroboam and all the people came to Rehoboam on the third day as the king had directed, saying, “Return to me on the third day.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The king answered them harshly, and King Rehoboam forsook the counsel of the elders.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He spoke to them according to the advice of the young men, saying, “My father made your yoke heavy, but I will add to it; my father disciplined you with whips, but I <i>will discipline you</i> with scorpions.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So the king did not listen to the people, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11411G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11411G\"></sup>for it was a turn <i>of events</i> from God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11411H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11411H\"></sup>that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> might establish His word, which He spoke through Ahijah the Shilonite to Jeroboam the son of Nebat.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When all Israel <i>saw</i> that the king did not listen to them the people answered the king, saying,“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11412I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11412I\"></sup>What portion do we have in David?<i>We have</i> no inheritance in the son of Jesse.Every man to your tents, O Israel;Now look after your own house, David.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11412J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11412J\"></sup>So all Israel departed to their tents.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But as for the sons of Israel who lived in the cities of Judah, Rehoboam reigned over them.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then King Rehoboam sent Hadoram, who was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11414K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11414K\"></sup>over the forced labor, and the sons of Israel stoned him to death. And King Rehoboam made haste to mount his chariot to flee to Jerusalem.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11415L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11415L\"></sup>Israel has been in rebellion against the house of David to this day."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11416A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11416A\"></sup>Now when Rehoboam had come to Jerusalem, he assembled the house of Judah and Benjamin, 180,000 chosen men who were warriors, to fight against Israel to restore the kingdom to Rehoboam.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>But the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11417B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11417B\"></sup>Shemaiah the man of God, saying,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“Speak to Rehoboam the son of Solomon, king of Judah, and to all Israel in Judah and Benjamin, saying,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “You shall not go up or fight against <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11419C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11419C\"></sup>your relatives; return every man to his house, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11419D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11419D\"></sup>for this thing is from Me.”’” So they listened to the words of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and returned from going against Jeroboam.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Rehoboam lived in Jerusalem and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11420E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11420E\"></sup>built cities for defense in Judah.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Thus he built Bethlehem, Etam, Tekoa,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Beth-zur, Soco, Adullam,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Gath, Mareshah, Ziph,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Adoraim, Lachish, Azekah,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Zorah, Aijalon and Hebron, which are fortified cities in Judah and in Benjamin.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He also strengthened the fortresses and put officers in them and stores of food, oil and wine.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><i>He put</i> shields and spears in every city and strengthened them greatly. So he held Judah and Benjamin.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Moreover, the priests and the Levites who were in all Israel stood with him from all their districts.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11429F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11429F\"></sup>the Levites left their pasture lands and their property and came to Judah and Jerusalem, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11429G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11429G\"></sup>Jeroboam and his sons had excluded them from serving as priests to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11430H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11430H\"></sup>He set up priests of his own for the high places, for the satyrs and for the calves which he had made.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11431I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11431I\"></sup>Those from all the tribes of Israel who set their hearts on seeking the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel followed them to Jerusalem, to sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of their fathers.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11432J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11432J\"></sup>They strengthened the kingdom of Judah and supported Rehoboam the son of Solomon for three years, for they walked in the way of David and Solomon for three years.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then Rehoboam took as a wife Mahalath the daughter of Jerimoth the son of David <i>and of</i> Abihail the daughter of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11433K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11433K\"></sup>Eliab the son of Jesse,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and she bore him sons: Jeush, Shemariah and Zaham.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>After her he took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11435L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11435L\"></sup>Maacah the daughter of Absalom, and she bore him Abijah, Attai, Ziza and Shelomith.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Rehoboam loved Maacah the daughter of Absalom more than all his <i>other</i> wives and concubines. For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11436M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11436M\"></sup>he had taken eighteen wives and sixty concubines and fathered twenty-eight sons and sixty daughters.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11437N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11437N\"></sup>Rehoboam appointed Abijah the son of Maacah as head and leader among his brothers, for he <i>intended</i> to make him king.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>He acted wisely and distributed some of his sons through all the territories of Judah and Benjamin to all the fortified cities, and he gave them food in abundance. And he sought many wives <i>for them</i>."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11439A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11439A\"></sup>When the kingdom of Rehoboam was established and strong, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11439B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11439B\"></sup>he and all Israel with him forsook the law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11440C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11440C\"></sup>And it came about in King Rehoboam’s fifth year, because they had been unfaithful to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11440D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11440D\"></sup>Shishak king of Egypt came up against Jerusalem",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>with 1,200 chariots and 60,000 horsemen. And the people who came with him from Egypt were without number: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11441E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11441E\"></sup>the Lubim, the Sukkiim and the Ethiopians.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He captured <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11442F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11442F\"></sup>the fortified cities of Judah and came as far as Jerusalem.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11443G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11443G\"></sup>Shemaiah the prophet came to Rehoboam and the princes of Judah who had gathered at Jerusalem because of Shishak, and he said to them, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11443H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11443H\"></sup>You have forsaken Me, so I also have forsaken you to Shishak.’”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So the princes of Israel and the king humbled themselves and said, “The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11444I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11444I\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is righteous.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> saw that they humbled themselves, the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to Shemaiah, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11445J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11445J\"></sup>They have humbled themselves <i>so</i> I will not destroy them, but I will grant them some <i>measure</i> of deliverance, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11445K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11445K\"></sup>My wrath shall not be poured out on Jerusalem by means of Shishak.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But they will become his slaves so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11446L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11446L\"></sup>that they may learn <i>the difference between</i> My service and the service of the kingdoms of the countries.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11447M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11447M\"></sup>So Shishak king of Egypt came up against Jerusalem, and took the treasures of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the treasures of the king’s palace. He took everything; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11447N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11447N\"></sup>he even took the golden shields which Solomon had made.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then King Rehoboam made shields of bronze in their place and committed them to the care of the commanders of the guard who guarded the door of the king’s house.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>As often as the king entered the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the guards came and carried them and <i>then</i> brought them back into the guards’ room.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11450O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11450O\"></sup>when he humbled himself, the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> turned away from him, so as not to destroy <i>him</i> completely; and also conditions <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11450P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11450P\"></sup>were good in Judah.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11451Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11451Q\"></sup>So King Rehoboam strengthened himself in Jerusalem and reigned. Now Rehoboam was forty-one years old when he began to reign, and he reigned seventeen years in Jerusalem, the city which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had chosen from all the tribes of Israel, to put His name there. And his mother’s name was Naamah the Ammonitess.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He did evil <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11452R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11452R\"></sup>because he did not set his heart to seek the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11453S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11453S\"></sup>Now the acts of Rehoboam, from first to last, are they not written in the records of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11453T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11453T\"></sup>Shemaiah the prophet and of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11453U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11453U\"></sup>Iddo the seer, according to genealogical enrollment? And <i>there were</i> wars between Rehoboam and Jeroboam continually.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And Rehoboam slept with his fathers and was buried in the city of David; and his son <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11454V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11454V\"></sup>Abijah became king in his place."
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11455A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11455A\"></sup>In the eighteenth year of King Jeroboam, Abijah became king over Judah.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He reigned three years in Jerusalem; and his mother’s name was Micaiah the daughter of Uriel of Gibeah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11456B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11456B\"></sup>Now there was war between Abijah and Jeroboam.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Abijah began the battle with an army of valiant warriors, 400,000 chosen men, while Jeroboam drew up in battle formation against him with 800,000 chosen men <i>who were</i> valiant warriors.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then Abijah stood on Mount <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11458C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11458C\"></sup>Zemaraim, which is in the hill country of Ephraim, and said, “Listen to me, Jeroboam and all Israel:",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Do you not know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11459D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11459D\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel gave the rule over Israel forever to David and his sons by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11459E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11459E\"></sup>a covenant of salt?",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Yet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11460F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11460F\"></sup>Jeroboam the son of Nebat, the servant of Solomon the son of David, rose up and rebelled against his master,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and worthless men gathered about him, scoundrels, who proved too strong for Rehoboam, the son of Solomon, when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11461G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11461G\"></sup>he was young and timid and could not hold his own against them.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“So now you intend to resist the kingdom of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> through the sons of David, being a great multitude and <i>having</i> with you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11462H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11462H\"></sup>the golden calves which Jeroboam made for gods for you.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11463I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11463I\"></sup>Have you not driven out the priests of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the sons of Aaron and the Levites, and made for yourselves priests like the peoples of <i>other</i> lands? Whoever comes <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11463J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11463J\"></sup>to consecrate himself with a young bull and seven rams, even he may become a priest of <i>what are</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11463K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11463K\"></sup>no gods.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But as for us, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is our God, and we have not forsaken Him; and the sons of Aaron are ministering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> as priests, and the Levites attend to their work.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Every morning and evening <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11465L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11465L\"></sup>they burn to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> burnt offerings and fragrant incense, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11465M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11465M\"></sup>the showbread is <i>set</i> on the clean table, and the golden lampstand with its lamps is <i>ready</i> to light every evening; for we keep the charge of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, but you have forsaken Him.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now behold, God is with us at <i>our</i> head and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11466N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11466N\"></sup>His priests with the signal trumpets to sound the alarm against you. O sons of Israel, do not fight against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of your fathers, for you will not succeed.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But Jeroboam <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11467O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11467O\"></sup>had set an ambush to come from the rear, so that <i>Israel</i> was in front of Judah and the ambush was behind them.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When Judah turned around, behold, they were attacked both front and rear; so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11468P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11468P\"></sup>they cried to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the priests blew the trumpets.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then the men of Judah raised a war cry, and when the men of Judah raised the war cry, then it was that God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11469Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11469Q\"></sup>routed Jeroboam and all Israel before Abijah and Judah.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When the sons of Israel fled before Judah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11470R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11470R\"></sup>God gave them into their hand.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Abijah and his people defeated them with a great slaughter, so that 500,000 chosen men of Israel fell slain.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Thus the sons of Israel were subdued at that time, and the sons of Judah conquered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11472S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11472S\"></sup>because they trusted in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their fathers.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Abijah pursued Jeroboam and captured from him <i>several</i> cities, Bethel with its villages, Jeshanah with its villages and Ephron with its villages.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Jeroboam did not again recover strength in the days of Abijah; and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11474T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11474T\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> struck him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11474U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11474U\"></sup>he died.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But Abijah became powerful; and took fourteen wives to himself, and became the father of twenty-two sons and sixteen daughters.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Abijah, and his ways and his words are written in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11476V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11476V\"></sup>the treatise of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11476W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11476W\"></sup>the prophet Iddo."
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11477A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11477A\"></sup>So Abijah slept with his fathers, and they buried him in the city of David, and his son Asa became king in his place. The land was undisturbed for ten years during his days.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Asa did good and right in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>for he removed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11479B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11479B\"></sup>the foreign altars and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11479C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11479C\"></sup>high places, tore down the <i>sacred</i> pillars, cut down the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11479D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11479D\"></sup>Asherim,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and commanded Judah to seek the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of their fathers and to observe the law and the commandment.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He also removed the high places and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11481E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11481E\"></sup>incense altars from all the cities of Judah. And the kingdom was undisturbed under him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11482F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11482F\"></sup>He built fortified cities in Judah, since the land was undisturbed, and there was no one at war with him during those years, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11482G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11482G\"></sup>because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had given him rest.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>For he said to Judah, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11483H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11483H\"></sup>Let us build these cities and surround <i>them</i> with walls and towers, gates and bars. The land is still ours because we have sought the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God; we have sought Him, and He has given us rest on every side.” So they built and prospered.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now Asa had an army of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11484I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11484I\"></sup>300,000 from Judah, bearing large shields and spears, and 280,000 from Benjamin, bearing shields and wielding bows; all of them were valiant warriors.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now Zerah the Ethiopian <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11485J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11485J\"></sup>came out against them with an army of a million men and 300 chariots, and he came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11485K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11485K\"></sup>Mareshah.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So Asa went out to meet him, and they drew up in battle formation in the valley of Zephathah at Mareshah.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then Asa <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11487L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11487L\"></sup>called to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God and said, “<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, there is no one besides You to help <i>in the battle</i> between the powerful and those who have no strength; so help us, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11487M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11487M\"></sup>for we trust in You, and in Your name have come against this multitude. O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, You are our God; let not man prevail against You.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11488N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11488N\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> routed the Ethiopians before Asa and before Judah, and the Ethiopians fled.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Asa and the people who <i>were</i> with him pursued them as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11489O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11489O\"></sup>Gerar; and so many Ethiopians fell that they could not recover, for they were shattered before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and before His army. And they carried away very much plunder.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>They destroyed all the cities around Gerar, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11490P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11490P\"></sup>for the dread of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had fallen on them; and they despoiled all the cities, for there was much plunder in them.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>They also struck down those who owned livestock, and they carried away large numbers of sheep and camels. Then they returned to Jerusalem."
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11492A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11492A\"></sup>the Spirit of God came on Azariah the son of Oded,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and he went out to meet Asa and said to him, “Listen to me, Asa, and all Judah and Benjamin: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11493B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11493B\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is with you when you are with Him. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11493C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11493C\"></sup>if you seek Him, He will let you find Him; but if you forsake Him, He will forsake you.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11494D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11494D\"></sup>For many days Israel was without the true God and without <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11494E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11494E\"></sup>a teaching priest and without law.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11495F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11495F\"></sup>in their distress they turned to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel, and they sought Him, and He let them find Him.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11496G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11496G\"></sup>In those times there was no peace to him who went out or to him who came in, for many disturbances afflicted all the inhabitants of the lands.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11497H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11497H\"></sup>Nation was crushed by nation, and city by city, for God troubled them with every kind of distress.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11498I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11498I\"></sup>be strong and do not lose courage, for there is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11498J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11498J\"></sup>reward for your work.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now when Asa heard these words and the prophecy which Azariah the son of Oded the prophet spoke, he took courage and removed the abominable idols from all the land of Judah and Benjamin and from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11499K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11499K\"></sup>the cities which he had captured in the hill country of Ephraim. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11499L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11499L\"></sup>He then restored the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> which was in front of the porch of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He gathered all Judah and Benjamin and those from Ephraim, Manasseh and Simeon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11500M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11500M\"></sup>who resided with them, for many defected to him from Israel when they saw that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God was with him.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So they assembled at Jerusalem in the third month of the fifteenth year of Asa’s reign.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11502N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11502N\"></sup>They sacrificed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that day 700 oxen and 7,000 sheep from the spoil they had brought.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11503O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11503O\"></sup>They entered into the covenant to seek the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of their fathers with all their heart and soul;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and whoever would not seek the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11504P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11504P\"></sup>should be put to death, whether small or great, man or woman.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Moreover, they made an oath to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with a loud voice, with shouting, with trumpets and with horns.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>All Judah rejoiced concerning the oath, for they had sworn with their whole heart and had sought Him earnestly, and He let them find Him. So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11506Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11506Q\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave them rest on every side.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11507R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11507R\"></sup>He also removed Maacah, the mother of King Asa, from the <i>position of</i> queen mother, because she had made a horrid image as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11507S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11507S\"></sup>an Asherah, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11507T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11507T\"></sup>Asa cut down her horrid image, crushed <i>it</i> and burned <i>it</i> at the brook Kidron.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But the high places were not removed from Israel; nevertheless Asa’s heart was blameless all his days.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He brought into the house of God the dedicated things of his father and his own dedicated things: silver and gold and utensils.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And there was no more war until the thirty-fifth year of Asa’s reign."
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>In the thirty-sixth year of Asa’s reign <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11511A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11511A\"></sup>Baasha king of Israel came up against Judah and fortified Ramah in order to prevent <i>anyone</i> from going out or coming in to Asa king of Judah.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then Asa brought out silver and gold from the treasuries of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the king’s house, and sent them to Ben-hadad king of Aram, who lived in Damascus, saying,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“<i>Let there be</i> a treaty between you and me, <i>as</i> between my father and your father. Behold, I have sent you silver and gold; go, break your treaty with Baasha king of Israel so that he will withdraw from me.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Ben-hadad listened to King Asa and sent the commanders of his armies against the cities of Israel, and they conquered Ijon, Dan, Abel-maim and all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11514B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11514B\"></sup>the store cities of Naphtali.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When Baasha heard <i>of it</i>, he ceased fortifying Ramah and stopped his work.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then King Asa brought all Judah, and they carried away the stones of Ramah and its timber with which Baasha had been building, and with them he fortified Geba and Mizpah.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>At that time <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11517C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11517C\"></sup>Hanani the seer came to Asa king of Judah and said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11517D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11517D\"></sup>Because you have relied on the king of Aram and have not relied on the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, therefore the army of the king of Aram has escaped out of your hand.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Were not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11518E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11518E\"></sup>the Ethiopians and the Lubim <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11518F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11518F\"></sup>an immense army with very many chariots and horsemen? Yet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11518G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11518G\"></sup>because you relied on the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, He delivered them into your hand.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11519H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11519H\"></sup>the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> move to and fro throughout the earth that He may strongly support those <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11519I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11519I\"></sup>whose heart is completely His. You have acted foolishly in this. Indeed, from now on you will surely have wars.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then Asa was angry with the seer and put him in prison, for he was enraged at him for this. And Asa oppressed some of the people at the same time.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11521J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11521J\"></sup>Now, the acts of Asa from first to last, behold, they are written in the Book of the Kings of Judah and Israel.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>In the thirty-ninth year of his reign Asa became diseased in his feet. His disease was severe, yet even in his disease he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11522K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11522K\"></sup>did not seek the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, but the physicians.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So Asa slept with his fathers, having died in the forty-first year of his reign.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>They buried him in his own tomb which he had cut out for himself in the city of David, and they laid him in the resting place which he had filled <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11524L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11524L\"></sup>with spices of various kinds blended by the perfumers’ art; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11524M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11524M\"></sup>they made a very great fire for him."
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11525A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11525A\"></sup>Jehoshaphat his son then became king in his place, and made his position over Israel firm.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He placed troops in all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11526B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11526B\"></sup>the fortified cities of Judah, and set garrisons in the land of Judah and in the cities of Ephraim <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11526C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11526C\"></sup>which Asa his father had captured.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with Jehoshaphat because he followed the example of his father David’s earlier days and did not seek the Baals,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>but sought the God of his father, followed His commandments, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11528D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11528D\"></sup>and did not act as Israel did.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> established the kingdom in his control, and all Judah brought tribute to Jehoshaphat, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11529E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11529E\"></sup>he had great riches and honor.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He took great pride in the ways of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and again <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11530F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11530F\"></sup>removed the high places and the Asherim from Judah.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then in the third year of his reign he sent his officials, Ben-hail, Obadiah, Zechariah, Nethanel and Micaiah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11531G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11531G\"></sup>to teach in the cities of Judah;",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and with them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11532H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11532H\"></sup>the Levites, Shemaiah, Nethaniah, Zebadiah, Asahel, Shemiramoth, Jehonathan, Adonijah, Tobijah and Tobadonijah, the Levites; and with them Elishama and Jehoram, the priests.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>They taught in Judah, <i>having</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11533I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11533I\"></sup>the book of the law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with them; and they went throughout all the cities of Judah and taught among the people.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11534J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11534J\"></sup>the dread of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was on all the kingdoms of the lands which <i>were</i> around Judah, so that they did not make war against Jehoshaphat.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Some of the Philistines <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11535K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11535K\"></sup>brought gifts and silver as tribute to Jehoshaphat; the Arabians also brought him flocks, 7,700 rams and 7,700 male goats.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So Jehoshaphat grew greater and greater, and he built fortresses and store cities in Judah.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He had large supplies in the cities of Judah, and warriors, valiant men, in Jerusalem.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>This was their muster according to their fathers’ households: of Judah, commanders of thousands, Adnah <i>was</i> the commander, and with him 300,000 valiant warriors;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and next to him <i>was</i> Johanan the commander, and with him 280,000;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and next to him Amasiah the son of Zichri, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11540L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11540L\"></sup>who volunteered for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and with him 200,000 valiant warriors;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and of Benjamin, Eliada a valiant warrior, and with him 200,000 armed with bow and shield;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and next to him Jehozabad, and with him 180,000 equipped for war.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>These are they who served the king, apart from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11543M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11543M\"></sup>those whom the king put in the fortified cities through all Judah."
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11544A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11544A\"></sup>Jehoshaphat had great riches and honor; and he allied himself by marriage with Ahab.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11545B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11545B\"></sup>Some years later he went down to <i>visit</i> Ahab at Samaria. And Ahab slaughtered many sheep and oxen for him and the people who were with him, and induced him to go up against Ramoth-gilead.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Ahab king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat king of Judah, “Will you go with me <i>against</i> Ramoth-gilead?” And he said to him, “I am as you are, and my people as your people, and <i>we will be</i> with you in the battle.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Moreover, Jehoshaphat said to the king of Israel, “Please inquire first for the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then the king of Israel assembled the prophets, four hundred men, and said to them, “Shall we go against Ramoth-gilead to battle, or shall I refrain?” And they said, “Go up, for God will give <i>it</i> into the hand of the king.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But Jehoshaphat said, “Is there not yet a prophet of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> here that we may inquire of him?”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, “There is yet one man by whom we may inquire of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, but I hate him, for he never prophesies good concerning me but always evil. He is Micaiah, son of Imla.” But Jehoshaphat said, “Let not the king say so.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then the king of Israel called an officer and said, “Bring quickly Micaiah, Imla’s son.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat the king of Judah were sitting each on his throne, arrayed in <i>their</i> robes, and <i>they</i> were sitting <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11552C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11552C\"></sup>at the threshing floor at the entrance of the gate of Samaria; and all the prophets were prophesying before them.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Zedekiah the son of Chenaanah made horns of iron for himself and said, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘With these you shall gore the Arameans until they are consumed.’”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>All the prophets were prophesying thus, saying, “Go up to Ramoth-gilead and succeed, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will give <i>it</i> into the hand of the king.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then the messenger who went to summon Micaiah spoke to him saying, “Behold, the words of the prophets are uniformly favorable to the king. So please let your word be like one of them and speak favorably.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But Micaiah said, “As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11556D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11556D\"></sup>what my God says, that I will speak.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When he came to the king, the king said to him, “Micaiah, shall we go to Ramoth-gilead to battle, or shall I refrain?” He said, “Go up and succeed, for they will be given into your hand.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then the king said to him, “How many times must I adjure you to speak to me nothing but the truth in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So he said,“I saw all IsraelScattered on the mountains,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11559E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11559E\"></sup>Like sheep which have no shepherd;And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said,‘These have no master.Let each of them return to his house in peace.’”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then the king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, “Did I not tell you that he would not prophesy good concerning me, but evil?”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Micaiah said, “Therefore, hear the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11561F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11561F\"></sup>I saw the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sitting on His throne, and all the host of heaven standing on His right and on His left.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, ‘Who will entice Ahab king of Israel to go up and fall at Ramoth-gilead?’ And one said this while another said that.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11563G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11563G\"></sup>spirit came forward and stood before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and said, ‘I will entice him.’ And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, ‘How?’",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He said, ‘I will go and be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11564H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11564H\"></sup>a deceiving spirit in the mouth of all his prophets.’ Then He said, ‘You are to entice <i>him</i> and prevail also. Go and do so.’",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Now therefore, behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11565I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11565I\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has put a deceiving spirit in the mouth of these your prophets, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has proclaimed disaster against you.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then Zedekiah the son of Chenaanah came near and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11566J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11566J\"></sup>struck Micaiah on the cheek and said, “How did the Spirit of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> pass from me to speak to you?”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Micaiah said, “Behold, you will see on that day when you enter an inner room to hide yourself.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then the king of Israel said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11568K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11568K\"></sup>Take Micaiah and return him to Amon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11568L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11568L\"></sup>the governor of the city and to Joash the king’s son;",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>and say, ‘Thus says the king, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11569M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11569M\"></sup>Put this <i>man</i> in prison and feed him sparingly with bread and water until I return safely.”’”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Micaiah said, “If you indeed return safely, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has not spoken by me.” And he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11570N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11570N\"></sup>Listen, all you people.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat king of Judah went up against Ramoth-gilead.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, “I will disguise myself and go into battle, but you put on your robes.” So the king of Israel disguised himself, and they went into battle.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Now the king of Aram had commanded the captains of his chariots, saying, “Do not fight with small or great, but with the king of Israel alone.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>So when the captains of the chariots saw Jehoshaphat, they said, “It is the king of Israel,” and they turned aside to fight against him. But Jehoshaphat <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11574O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11574O\"></sup>cried out, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> helped him, and God diverted them from him.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>When the captains of the chariots saw that it was not the king of Israel, they turned back from pursuing him.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>A certain man drew his bow at random and struck the king of Israel in a joint of the armor. So he said to the driver of the chariot, “Turn around and take me out of the fight, for I am severely wounded.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>The battle raged that day, and the king of Israel propped himself up in his chariot in front of the Arameans until the evening; and at sunset he died."
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span>Then Jehoshaphat the king of Judah returned in safety to his house in Jerusalem.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11579A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11579A\"></sup>Jehu the son of Hanani the seer went out to meet him and said to King Jehoshaphat, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11579B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11579B\"></sup>Should you help the wicked and love those who hate the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11579C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11579C\"></sup>so <i>bring</i> wrath on yourself from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11580D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11580D\"></sup>there is <i>some</i> good in you, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11580E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11580E\"></sup>you have removed the Asheroth from the land and you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11580F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11580F\"></sup>have set your heart to seek God.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Jehoshaphat lived in Jerusalem and went out again among the people from Beersheba to the hill country of Ephraim and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11581G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11581G\"></sup>brought them back to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their fathers.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He appointed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11582H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11582H\"></sup>judges in the land in all the fortified cities of Judah, city by city.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He said to the judges, “Consider what you are doing, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11583I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11583I\"></sup>you do not judge for man but for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who is with you when you render judgment.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now then let the fear of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> be upon you; be very careful what you do, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11584J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11584J\"></sup>have no part in unrighteousness <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11584K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11584K\"></sup>or partiality or the taking of a bribe.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>In Jerusalem also Jehoshaphat appointed some <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11585L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11585L\"></sup>of the Levites and priests, and some of the heads of the fathers’ <i>households</i> of Israel, for the judgment of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and to judge disputes among the inhabitants of Jerusalem.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then he charged them saying, “Thus you shall do in the fear of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, faithfully and wholeheartedly.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11587M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11587M\"></sup>Whenever any dispute comes to you from your brethren who live in their cities, between blood and blood, between law and commandment, statutes and ordinances, you shall warn them so that they may not be guilty before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11587N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11587N\"></sup>wrath may <i>not</i> come on you and your brethren. Thus you shall do and you will not be guilty.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Behold, Amariah the chief priest will be over you in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11588O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11588O\"></sup>all that pertains to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and Zebadiah the son of Ishmael, the ruler of the house of Judah, in all that pertains to the king. Also the Levites shall be officers before you. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11588P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11588P\"></sup>Act resolutely, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> be with the upright.”"
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span>Now it came about after this that the sons of Moab and the sons of Ammon, together with some of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11589A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11589A\"></sup>Meunites, came to make war against Jehoshaphat.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then some came and reported to Jehoshaphat, saying, “A great multitude is coming against you from beyond the sea, out of Aram and behold, they are in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11590B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11590B\"></sup>Hazazon-tamar (that is Engedi).”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Jehoshaphat was afraid and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11591C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11591C\"></sup>turned his attention to seek the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11591D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11591D\"></sup>proclaimed a fast throughout all Judah.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Judah gathered together to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11592E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11592E\"></sup>seek help from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; they even came from all the cities of Judah to seek the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then Jehoshaphat stood in the assembly of Judah and Jerusalem, in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> before the new court,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and he said, “O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of our fathers, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11594F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11594F\"></sup>are You not God in the heavens? And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11594G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11594G\"></sup>are You not ruler over all the kingdoms of the nations? Power and might are in Your hand so that no one can stand against You.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Did You not, O our God, drive out the inhabitants of this land before Your people Israel and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11595H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11595H\"></sup>give it to the descendants of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11595I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11595I\"></sup>Abraham Your friend forever?",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>They have lived in it, and have built You a sanctuary there for Your name, saying,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11597J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11597J\"></sup>Should evil come upon us, the sword, <i>or</i> judgment, or pestilence, or famine, we will stand before this house and before You (for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11597K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11597K\"></sup>Your name is in this house) and cry to You in our distress, and You will hear and deliver <i>us</i>.’",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11598L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11598L\"></sup>the sons of Ammon and Moab and Mount Seir, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11598M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11598M\"></sup>whom You did not let Israel invade when they came out of the land of Egypt (they turned aside from them and did not destroy them),",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>see <i>how</i> they are rewarding us by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11599N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11599N\"></sup>coming to drive us out from Your possession which You have given us as an inheritance.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>O our God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11600O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11600O\"></sup>will You not judge them? For we are powerless before this great multitude who are coming against us; nor do we know what to do, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11600P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11600P\"></sup>our eyes are on You.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>All Judah was standing before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, with their infants, their wives and their children.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then in the midst of the assembly <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11602Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11602Q\"></sup>the Spirit of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came upon Jahaziel the son of Zechariah, the son of Benaiah, the son of Jeiel, the son of Mattaniah, the Levite of the sons of Asaph;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and he said, “Listen, all Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem and King Jehoshaphat: thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to you, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11603R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11603R\"></sup>Do not fear or be dismayed because of this great multitude, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11603S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11603S\"></sup>the battle is not yours but God’s.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Tomorrow go down against them. Behold, they will come up by the ascent of Ziz, and you will find them at the end of the valley in front of the wilderness of Jeruel.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>You <i>need</i> not fight in this <i>battle</i>; station yourselves, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11605T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11605T\"></sup>stand and see the salvation of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on your behalf, O Judah and Jerusalem.’ Do not fear or be dismayed; tomorrow go out to face them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11605U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11605U\"></sup>for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is with you.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Jehoshaphat <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11606V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11606V\"></sup>bowed his head with <i>his</i> face to the ground, and all Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem fell down before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, worshiping the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The Levites, from the sons of the Kohathites and of the sons of the Korahites, stood up to praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel, with a very loud voice.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>They rose early in the morning and went out to the wilderness of Tekoa; and when they went out, Jehoshaphat stood and said, “Listen to me, O Judah and inhabitants of Jerusalem, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11608W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11608W\"></sup>put your trust in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God and you will be established. Put your trust in His prophets and succeed.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When he had consulted with the people, he appointed those who sang to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and those who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11609X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11609X\"></sup>praised <i>Him</i> in holy attire, as they went out before the army and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11609Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11609Y\"></sup>Give thanks to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for His lovingkindness is everlasting.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>When they began singing and praising, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11610Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11610Z\"></sup>set ambushes against the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11610AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11610AA\"></sup>Ammon, Moab and Mount Seir, who had come against Judah; so they were routed.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>For the sons of Ammon and Moab rose up against the inhabitants of Mount Seir destroying <i>them</i> completely; and when they had finished with the inhabitants of Seir, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11611AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11611AB\"></sup>they helped to destroy one another.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>When Judah came to the lookout of the wilderness, they looked toward the multitude, and behold, they <i>were</i> corpses lying on the ground, and no one had escaped.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>When Jehoshaphat and his people came to take their spoil, they found much among them, <i>including</i> goods, garments and valuable things which they took for themselves, more than they could carry. And they were three days taking the spoil because there was so much.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then on the fourth day they assembled in the valley of Beracah, for there they blessed the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Therefore they have named that place “The Valley of Beracah” until today.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Every man of Judah and Jerusalem returned with Jehoshaphat at their head, returning to Jerusalem with joy, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11615AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11615AC\"></sup>for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had made them to rejoice over their enemies.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>They came to Jerusalem with harps, lyres and trumpets to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11617AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11617AD\"></sup>the dread of God was on all the kingdoms of the lands when they heard that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had fought against the enemies of Israel.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>So the kingdom of Jehoshaphat was at peace, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11618AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11618AE\"></sup>for his God gave him rest on all sides.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11619AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11619AF\"></sup>Now Jehoshaphat reigned over Judah. He <i>was</i> thirty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem twenty-five years. And his mother’s name <i>was</i> Azubah the daughter of Shilhi.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>He walked in the way of his father Asa and did not depart from it, doing right in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11621AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11621AG\"></sup>The high places, however, were not removed; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11621AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11621AH\"></sup>the people had not yet directed their hearts to the God of their fathers.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Jehoshaphat, first to last, behold, they are written in the annals of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11622AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11622AI\"></sup>Jehu the son of Hanani, which is recorded in the Book of the Kings of Israel.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11623AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11623AJ\"></sup>After this Jehoshaphat king of Judah allied himself with Ahaziah king of Israel. He acted wickedly in so doing.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>So he allied himself with him to make ships to go <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11624AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11624AK\"></sup>to Tarshish, and they made the ships in Ezion-geber.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Then Eliezer the son of Dodavahu of Mareshah prophesied against Jehoshaphat saying, “Because you have allied yourself with Ahaziah, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has destroyed your works.” So the ships were broken and could not go to Tarshish."
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11626A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11626A\"></sup>Then Jehoshaphat slept with his fathers and was buried with his fathers in the city of David, and Jehoram his son became king in his place.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He had brothers, the sons of Jehoshaphat: Azariah, Jehiel, Zechariah, Azaryahu, Michael and Shephatiah. All these <i>were</i> the sons of Jehoshaphat king <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11627B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11627B\"></sup>of Israel.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Their father gave them many gifts of silver, gold and precious things, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11628C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11628C\"></sup>with fortified cities in Judah, but he gave the kingdom to Jehoram because he was the firstborn.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Now when Jehoram had taken over the kingdom of his father and made himself secure, he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11629D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11629D\"></sup>killed all his brothers with the sword, and some of the rulers of Israel also.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11630E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11630E\"></sup>Jehoram <i>was</i> thirty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned eight years in Jerusalem.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11631F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11631F\"></sup>He walked in the way of the kings of Israel, just as the house of Ahab did (<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11631G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11631G\"></sup>for Ahab’s daughter was his wife), and he did evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Yet the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was not willing to destroy the house of David because of the covenant which He had made with David, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11632H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11632H\"></sup>and since He had promised to give a lamp to him and his sons forever.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>In his days <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11633I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11633I\"></sup>Edom revolted against the rule of Judah and set up a king over themselves.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then Jehoram crossed over with his commanders and all his chariots with him. And he arose by night and struck down the Edomites who were surrounding him and the commanders of the chariots.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So Edom revolted against Judah to this day. Then Libnah revolted at the same time against his rule, because he had forsaken the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of his fathers.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Moreover, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11636J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11636J\"></sup>he made high places in the mountains of Judah, and caused the inhabitants of Jerusalem <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11636K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11636K\"></sup>to play the harlot and led Judah astray.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then a letter came to him from Elijah the prophet saying, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of your father David, ‘Because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11637L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11637L\"></sup>you have not walked in the ways of Jehoshaphat your father <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11637M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11637M\"></sup>and the ways of Asa king of Judah,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11638N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11638N\"></sup>have walked in the way of the kings of Israel, and have caused Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem to play the harlot <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11638O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11638O\"></sup>as the house of Ahab played the harlot, and you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11638P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11638P\"></sup>have also killed your brothers, your own family, who were better than you,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>behold, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is going to strike your people, your sons, your wives and all your possessions with a great calamity;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11640Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11640Q\"></sup>you will suffer severe sickness, a disease of your bowels, until your bowels come out because of the sickness, day by day.’”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11641R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11641R\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> stirred up against Jehoram the spirit of the Philistines and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11641S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11641S\"></sup>the Arabs who bordered the Ethiopians;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and they came against Judah and invaded it, and carried away all the possessions found in the king’s house together with his sons and his wives, so that no son was left to him except <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11642T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11642T\"></sup>Jehoahaz, the youngest of his sons.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So after all this the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> smote him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11643U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11643U\"></sup>in his bowels with an incurable sickness.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now it came about in the course of time, at the end of two years, that his bowels came out because of his sickness and he died in great pain. And his people made no fire for him like <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11644V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11644V\"></sup>the fire for his fathers.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>He was thirty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem eight years; and he departed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11645W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11645W\"></sup>with no one’s regret, and they buried him in the city of David, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11645X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11645X\"></sup>but not in the tombs of the kings."
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">22 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11646A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11646A\"></sup>Then the inhabitants of Jerusalem made Ahaziah, his youngest son, king in his place, for the band of men who came with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11646B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11646B\"></sup>the Arabs to the camp had slain all the older <i>sons</i>. So Ahaziah the son of Jehoram king of Judah began to reign.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Ahaziah <i>was</i> twenty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned one year in Jerusalem. And his mother’s name was Athaliah, the granddaughter of Omri.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He also walked in the ways of the house of Ahab, for his mother was his counselor to do wickedly.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He did evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> like the house of Ahab, for they were his counselors after the death of his father, to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11649C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11649C\"></sup>his destruction.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He also walked according to their counsel, and went with Jehoram the son of Ahab king of Israel to wage war against Hazael king of Aram at Ramoth-gilead. But the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11650D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11650D\"></sup>Arameans wounded Joram.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So he returned to be healed in Jezreel of the wounds which they had inflicted on him at Ramah, when he fought against Hazael king of Aram. And Ahaziah, the son of Jehoram king of Judah, went down to see Jehoram the son of Ahab in Jezreel, because he was sick.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11652E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11652E\"></sup>the destruction of Ahaziah was from God, in that he went to Joram. For when he came, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11652F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11652F\"></sup>he went out with Jehoram against Jehu the son of Nimshi, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11652G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11652G\"></sup>whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had anointed to cut off the house of Ahab.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11653H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11653H\"></sup>It came about when Jehu was executing judgment on the house of Ahab, he found the princes of Judah and the sons of Ahaziah’s brothers ministering to Ahaziah, and slew them.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11654I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11654I\"></sup>He also sought Ahaziah, and they caught him while he was hiding in Samaria; they brought him to Jehu, put him to death <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11654J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11654J\"></sup>and buried him. For they said, “He is the son of Jehoshaphat, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11654K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11654K\"></sup>who sought the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with all his heart.” So there was no one of the house of Ahaziah to retain the power of the kingdom.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11655L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11655L\"></sup>Now when Athaliah the mother of Ahaziah saw that her son was dead, she rose and destroyed all the royal offspring of the house of Judah.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But Jehoshabeath the king’s daughter took Joash the son of Ahaziah, and stole him from among the king’s sons who were being put to death, and placed him and his nurse in the bedroom. So Jehoshabeath, the daughter of King Jehoram, the wife of Jehoiada the priest (for she was the sister of Ahaziah), hid him from Athaliah so that she would not put him to death.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He was hidden with them in the house of God six years while Athaliah reigned over the land."
		},
		"23": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">23 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11658A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11658A\"></sup>Now in the seventh year Jehoiada strengthened himself, and took captains of hundreds: Azariah the son of Jeroham, Ishmael the son of Johanan, Azariah the son of Obed, Maaseiah the son of Adaiah, and Elishaphat the son of Zichri, <i>and they entered</i> into a covenant with him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>They went throughout Judah and gathered the Levites from all the cities of Judah, and the heads of the fathers’ <i>households</i> of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11659B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11659B\"></sup>Israel, and they came to Jerusalem.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then all the assembly made a covenant with the king in the house of God. And Jehoiada said to them, “Behold, the king’s son shall reign, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11660C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11660C\"></sup>as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has spoken concerning the sons of David.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>This is the thing which you shall do: one third of you, of the priests and Levites <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11661D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11661D\"></sup>who come in on the sabbath, <i>shall be</i> gatekeepers,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and one third <i>shall be</i> at the king’s house, and a third at the Gate of the Foundation; and all the people <i>shall be</i> in the courts of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But let no one enter the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> except the priests and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11663E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11663E\"></sup>the ministering Levites; they may enter, for they are holy. And let all the people keep the charge of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The Levites will surround the king, each man with his weapons in his hand; and whoever enters the house, let him be killed. Thus be with the king when he comes in and when he goes out.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So the Levites and all Judah did according to all that Jehoiada the priest commanded. And each one of them took his men who were to come in on the sabbath, with those who were to go out on the sabbath, for Jehoiada the priest did not dismiss <i>any of</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11665F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11665F\"></sup>the divisions.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then Jehoiada the priest gave to the captains of hundreds the spears and the large and small shields which had been King David’s, which were in the house of God.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He stationed all the people, each man with his weapon in his hand, from the right side of the house to the left side of the house, by the altar and by the house, around the king.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then they brought out the king’s son and put the crown on him, and <i>gave him</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11668G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11668G\"></sup>the testimony and made him king. And Jehoiada and his sons anointed him and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11668H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11668H\"></sup><i>Long</i> live the king!”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When Athaliah heard the noise of the people running and praising the king, she came into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to the people.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>She looked, and behold, the king was standing by his pillar at the entrance, and the captains and the trumpeters <i>were</i> beside the king. And all the people of the land rejoiced and blew trumpets, the singers with <i>their</i> musical instruments leading the praise. Then Athaliah tore her clothes and said, “Treason! Treason!”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Jehoiada the priest brought out the captains of hundreds who were appointed over the army and said to them, “Bring her out between the ranks; and whoever follows her, put to death with the sword.” For the priest said, “Let her not be put to death in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So they seized her, and when she arrived at the entrance of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11672I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11672I\"></sup>the Horse Gate of the king’s house, they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11672J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11672J\"></sup>put her to death there.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11673K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11673K\"></sup>Jehoiada made a covenant between himself and all the people and the king, that they would be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> people.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And all the people went to the house of Baal and tore it down, and they broke in pieces his altars and his images, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11674L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11674L\"></sup>killed Mattan the priest of Baal before the altars.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Moreover, Jehoiada placed the offices of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> under the authority of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11675M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11675M\"></sup>the Levitical priests, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11675N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11675N\"></sup>whom David had assigned over the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, to offer the burnt offerings of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as it is written in the law of Moses—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11675O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11675O\"></sup>with rejoicing and singing according to the order of David.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He stationed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11676P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11676P\"></sup>the gatekeepers of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, so that no one would enter <i>who was</i> in any way unclean.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11677Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11677Q\"></sup>He took the captains of hundreds, the nobles, the rulers of the people and all the people of the land, and brought the king down from the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and came through the upper gate to the king’s house. And they placed the king upon the royal throne.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11678R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11678R\"></sup>all of the people of the land rejoiced and the city was quiet. For they had put Athaliah to death with the sword."
		},
		"24": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">24 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11679A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11679A\"></sup>Joash <i>was</i> seven years old when he became king, and he reigned forty years in Jerusalem; and his mother’s name <i>was</i> Zibiah from Beersheba.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11680B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11680B\"></sup>Joash did what was right in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> all the days of Jehoiada the priest.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Jehoiada took two wives for him, and he became the father of sons and daughters.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Now it came about after this that Joash decided <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11682C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11682C\"></sup>to restore the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He gathered the priests and Levites and said to them, “Go out to the cities of Judah and collect money from all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11683D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11683D\"></sup>Israel to repair the house of your God annually, and you shall do the matter quickly.” But the Levites did not act quickly.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So the king summoned Jehoiada the chief <i>priest</i> and said to him, “Why have you not required the Levites to bring in from Judah and from Jerusalem <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11684E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11684E\"></sup>the levy <i>fixed by</i> Moses the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on the congregation of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11684F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11684F\"></sup>for the tent of the testimony?”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11685G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11685G\"></sup>the sons of the wicked Athaliah had broken into the house of God and even used the holy things of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for the Baals.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So the king commanded, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11686H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11686H\"></sup>they made a chest and set it outside by the gate of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11687I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11687I\"></sup>They made a proclamation in Judah and Jerusalem to bring to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11687J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11687J\"></sup>the levy <i>fixed by</i> Moses the servant of God on Israel in the wilderness.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>All the officers and all the people rejoiced and brought in their levies and dropped <i>them</i> into the chest until they had finished.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>It came about whenever the chest was brought in to the king’s officer by the Levites, and when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11689K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11689K\"></sup>they saw that there was much money, then the king’s scribe and the chief priest’s officer would come, empty the chest, take it, and return it to its place. Thus they did daily and collected much money.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The king and Jehoiada gave it to those who did the work of the service of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; and they hired masons and carpenters to restore the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and also workers in iron and bronze to repair the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So the workmen labored, and the repair work progressed in their hands, and they restored the house of God according to its specifications and strengthened it.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When they had finished, they brought the rest of the money before the king and Jehoiada; and it was made into utensils for the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, utensils for the service and the burnt offering, and pans and utensils of gold and silver. And they offered burnt offerings in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> continually all the days of Jehoiada.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now when Jehoiada reached a ripe old age he died; he was one hundred and thirty years old at his death.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>They buried him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11694L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11694L\"></sup>in the city of David among the kings, because he had done well in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11694M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11694M\"></sup>Israel and to God and His house.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But after the death of Jehoiada the officials of Judah came and bowed down to the king, and the king listened to them.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>They abandoned <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11696N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11696N\"></sup>the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their fathers, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11696O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11696O\"></sup>served the Asherim and the idols; so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11696P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11696P\"></sup>wrath came upon Judah and Jerusalem for this their guilt.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Yet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11697Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11697Q\"></sup>He sent prophets to them to bring them back to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; though they testified against them, they would not listen.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11698R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11698R\"></sup>Then the Spirit of God came on Zechariah the son of Jehoiada the priest; and he stood above the people and said to them, “Thus God has said, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11698S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11698S\"></sup>Why do you transgress the commandments of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and do not prosper? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11698T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11698T\"></sup>Because you have forsaken the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, He has also forsaken you.’”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11699U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11699U\"></sup>they conspired against him and at the command of the king they stoned him to death in the court of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Thus Joash the king did not remember the kindness which his father Jehoiada had shown him, but he murdered his son. And as he died he said, “May <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11700V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11700V\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> see and avenge!”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Now it happened at the turn of the year that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11701W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11701W\"></sup>the army of the Arameans came up against him; and they came to Judah and Jerusalem, destroyed all the officials of the people from among the people, and sent all their spoil to the king of Damascus.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Indeed the army of the Arameans came with a small number of men; yet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11702X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11702X\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> delivered a very great army into their hands, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11702Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11702Y\"></sup>because they had forsaken the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their fathers. Thus they executed judgment on Joash.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11703Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11703Z\"></sup>When they had departed from him (for they left him very sick), his own servants conspired against him because of the blood of the son of Jehoiada the priest, and murdered him on his bed. So he died, and they buried him in the city of David, but they did not bury him in the tombs of the kings.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Now these are those who conspired against him: Zabad the son of Shimeath the Ammonitess, and Jehozabad the son of Shimrith the Moabitess.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>As to his sons and the many oracles against him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11705AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11705AA\"></sup>the rebuilding of the house of God, behold, they are written in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11705AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11705AB\"></sup>treatise of the Book of the Kings. Then Amaziah his son became king in his place."
		},
		"25": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">25 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11706A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11706A\"></sup>Amaziah was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned twenty-nine years in Jerusalem. And his mother’s name was Jehoaddan of Jerusalem.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He did right in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11707B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11707B\"></sup>yet not with a whole heart.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11708C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11708C\"></sup>it came about as soon as the kingdom was firmly in his grasp, that he killed his servants who had slain his father the king.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>However, he did not put their children to death, but <i>did</i> as it is written in the law in the book of Moses, which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11709D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11709D\"></sup>Fathers shall not be put to death for sons, nor sons be put to death for fathers, but each shall be put to death for his own sin.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Moreover, Amaziah assembled Judah and appointed them according to <i>their</i> fathers’ households under commanders of thousands and commanders of hundreds throughout Judah and Benjamin; and he took a census of those <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11710E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11710E\"></sup>from twenty years old and upward and found them to be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11710F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11710F\"></sup>300,000 choice men, <i>able</i> to go to war <i>and</i> handle spear and shield.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He hired also 100,000 valiant warriors out of Israel for one hundred talents of silver.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11712G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11712G\"></sup>a man of God came to him saying, “O king, do not let the army of Israel go with you, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is not with Israel <i>nor with</i> any of the sons of Ephraim.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But if you do go, do <i>it</i>, be strong for the battle; <i>yet</i> God will bring you down before the enemy, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11713H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11713H\"></sup>for God has power to help and to bring down.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Amaziah said to the man of God, “But what <i>shall we</i> do for the hundred talents which I have given to the troops of Israel?” And the man of God answered, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11714I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11714I\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has much more to give you than this.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then Amaziah dismissed them, the troops which came to him from Ephraim, to go home; so their anger burned against Judah and they returned home in fierce anger.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now Amaziah strengthened himself and led his people forth, and went to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11716J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11716J\"></sup>the Valley of Salt and struck down 10,000 of the sons of Seir.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The sons of Judah also captured 10,000 alive and brought them to the top of the cliff and threw them down from the top of the cliff, so that they were all dashed to pieces.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But the troops whom Amaziah sent back from going with him to battle, raided the cities of Judah, from Samaria to Beth-horon, and struck down 3,000 of them and plundered much spoil.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Now after Amaziah came from slaughtering the Edomites, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11719K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11719K\"></sup>he brought the gods of the sons of Seir, set them up as his gods, bowed down before them and burned incense to them.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> burned against Amaziah, and He sent him a prophet who said to him, “Why have you sought the gods of the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11720L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11720L\"></sup>who have not delivered their own people from your hand?”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>As he was talking with him, the king said to him, “Have we appointed you a royal counselor? Stop! Why should you be struck down?” Then the prophet stopped and said, “I know that God has planned to destroy you, because you have done this and have not listened to my counsel.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11722M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11722M\"></sup>Then Amaziah king of Judah took counsel and sent to Joash the son of Jehoahaz the son of Jehu, the king of Israel, saying, “Come, let us face each other.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Joash the king of Israel sent to Amaziah king of Judah, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11723N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11723N\"></sup>The thorn bush which was in Lebanon sent to the cedar which was in Lebanon, saying, ‘Give your daughter to my son in marriage.’ But there passed by a wild beast that was in Lebanon and trampled the thorn bush.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>You said, ‘Behold, you have defeated Edom.’ And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11724O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11724O\"></sup>your heart has become proud in boasting. Now stay at home; for why should you provoke trouble so that you, even you, would fall and Judah with you?”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But Amaziah would not listen, for it was from God, that He might deliver them into the hand <i>of Joash</i> because they had sought the gods of Edom.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So Joash king of Israel went up, and he and Amaziah king of Judah faced each other at Beth-shemesh, which belonged to Judah.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Judah was defeated by Israel, and they fled each to his tent.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then Joash king of Israel captured Amaziah king of Judah, the son of Joash the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11728P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11728P\"></sup>Jehoahaz, at Beth-shemesh, and brought him to Jerusalem and tore down the wall of Jerusalem from the Gate of Ephraim to the Corner Gate, 400 cubits.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><i>He took</i> all the gold and silver and all the utensils which were found in the house of God with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11729Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11729Q\"></sup>Obed-edom, and the treasures of the king’s house, the hostages also, and returned to Samaria.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11730R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11730R\"></sup>And Amaziah, the son of Joash king of Judah, lived fifteen years after the death of Joash, son of Jehoahaz, king of Israel.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Amaziah, from first to last, behold, are they not written in the Book of the Kings of Judah and Israel?",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>From the time that Amaziah turned away from following the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> they conspired against him in Jerusalem, and he fled to Lachish; but they sent after him to Lachish and killed him there.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then they brought him on horses and buried him with his fathers in the city of Judah."
		},
		"26": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">26 </span>And all the people of Judah took Uzziah, who <i>was</i> sixteen years old, and made him king in the place of his father Amaziah.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He built Eloth and restored it to Judah after the king slept with his fathers.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Uzziah was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11736A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11736A\"></sup>sixteen years old when he became king, and he reigned fifty-two years in Jerusalem; and his mother’s name was Jechiliah of Jerusalem.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He did right in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> according to all that his father Amaziah had done.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11738B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11738B\"></sup>He continued to seek God in the days of Zechariah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11738C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11738C\"></sup>who had understanding through the vision of God; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11738D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11738D\"></sup>as long as he sought the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, God prospered him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Now he went out and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11739E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11739E\"></sup>warred against the Philistines, and broke down the wall of Gath and the wall of Jabneh and the wall of Ashdod; and he built cities in <i>the area of</i> Ashdod and among the Philistines.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11740F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11740F\"></sup>God helped him against the Philistines, and against the Arabians who lived in Gur-baal, and the Meunites.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The Ammonites also gave <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11741G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11741G\"></sup>tribute to Uzziah, and his fame extended to the border of Egypt, for he became very strong.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Moreover, Uzziah built towers in Jerusalem at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11742H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11742H\"></sup>the Corner Gate and at the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11742I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11742I\"></sup>Valley Gate and at the corner buttress and fortified them.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He built towers in the wilderness and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11743J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11743J\"></sup>hewed many cisterns, for he had much livestock, both in the lowland and in the plain. <i>He also had</i> plowmen and vinedressers in the hill country and the fertile fields, for he loved the soil.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Moreover, Uzziah had an army ready for battle, which entered combat by divisions according to the number of their muster, prepared by Jeiel the scribe and Maaseiah the official, under the direction of Hananiah, one of the king’s officers.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The total number of the heads of the households, of valiant warriors, was 2,600.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Under their direction was an elite army of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11746K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11746K\"></sup>307,500, who could wage war with great power, to help the king against the enemy.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Moreover, Uzziah prepared for all the army shields, spears, helmets, body armor, bows and sling stones.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>In Jerusalem he made engines <i>of war</i> invented by skillful men to be on the towers and on the corners for the purpose of shooting arrows and great stones. Hence his fame spread afar, for he was marvelously helped until he <i>was</i> strong.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11749L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11749L\"></sup>when he became strong, his heart was so proud that he acted corruptly, and he was unfaithful to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11749M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11749M\"></sup>he entered the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to burn incense on the altar of incense.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11750N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11750N\"></sup>Azariah the priest entered after him and with him eighty priests of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, valiant men.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11751O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11751O\"></sup>They opposed Uzziah the king and said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11751P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11751P\"></sup>It is not for you, Uzziah, to burn incense to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11751Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11751Q\"></sup>but for the priests, the sons of Aaron who are consecrated to burn incense. Get out of the sanctuary, for you have been unfaithful and will have no honor from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But Uzziah, with a censer in his hand for burning incense, was enraged; and while he was enraged with the priests, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11752R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11752R\"></sup>the leprosy broke out on his forehead before the priests in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, beside the altar of incense.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Azariah the chief priest and all the priests looked at him, and behold, he <i>was</i> leprous on his forehead; and they hurried him out of there, and he himself also hastened to get out because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had smitten him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11754S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11754S\"></sup>King Uzziah was a leper to the day of his death; and he lived in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11754T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11754T\"></sup>a separate house, being a leper, for he was cut off from the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. And Jotham his son <i>was</i> over the king’s house judging the people of the land.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Uzziah, first to last, the prophet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11755U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11755U\"></sup>Isaiah, the son of Amoz, has written.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So Uzziah slept with his fathers, and they buried him with his fathers <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11756V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11756V\"></sup>in the field of the grave which belonged to the kings, for they said, “He is a leper.” And Jotham his son became king in his place."
		},
		"27": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">27 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11757A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11757A\"></sup>Jotham was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned sixteen years in Jerusalem. And his mother’s name was Jerushah the daughter of Zadok.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He did right in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, according to all that his father Uzziah had done; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11758B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11758B\"></sup>however he did not enter the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. But the people continued acting corruptly.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He built the upper gate of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and he built extensively the wall of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11759C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11759C\"></sup>Ophel.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Moreover, he built <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11760D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11760D\"></sup>cities in the hill country of Judah, and he built fortresses and towers on the wooded <i>hills</i>.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He fought also with the king of the Ammonites and prevailed over them so that the Ammonites gave him during that year one hundred talents of silver, ten thousand kors of wheat and ten thousand of barley. The Ammonites also paid him this <i>amount</i> in the second and in the third year.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11762E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11762E\"></sup>So Jotham became mighty because he ordered his ways before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11763F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11763F\"></sup>Now the rest of the acts of Jotham, even all his wars and his acts, behold, they are written in the Book of the Kings of Israel and Judah.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11764G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11764G\"></sup>twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned sixteen years in Jerusalem.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Jotham slept with his fathers, and they buried him in the city of David; and Ahaz his son became king in his place."
		},
		"28": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">28 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11766A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11766A\"></sup>Ahaz <i>was</i> twenty years old when he became king, and he reigned sixteen years in Jerusalem; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11766B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11766B\"></sup>he did not do right in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> as David his father <i>had done</i>.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11767C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11767C\"></sup>But he walked in the ways of the kings of Israel; he also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11767D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11767D\"></sup>made molten images for the Baals.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Moreover, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11768E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11768E\"></sup>he burned incense in the valley of Ben-hinnom and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11768F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11768F\"></sup>burned his sons in fire, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11768G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11768G\"></sup>according to the abominations of the nations whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had driven out before the sons of Israel.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He sacrificed and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11769H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11769H\"></sup>burned incense on the high places, on the hills and under every green tree.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Wherefore, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11770I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11770I\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God delivered him into the hand of the king of Aram; and they defeated him and carried away from him a great number of captives and brought <i>them</i> to Damascus. And he was also delivered into the hand of the king of Israel, who inflicted him with heavy casualties.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11771J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11771J\"></sup>Pekah the son of Remaliah slew in Judah 120,000 in one day, all valiant men, because they had forsaken the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of their fathers.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And Zichri, a mighty man of Ephraim, slew Maaseiah the king’s son and Azrikam the ruler of the house and Elkanah the second to the king.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11773K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11773K\"></sup>The sons of Israel carried away captive of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11773L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11773L\"></sup>their brethren 200,000 women, sons and daughters; and they took also a great deal of spoil from them, and brought the spoil to Samaria.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But a prophet of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was there, whose name <i>was</i> Oded; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11774M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11774M\"></sup>he went out to meet the army which came to Samaria and said to them, “Behold, because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of your fathers, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11774N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11774N\"></sup>was angry with Judah, He has delivered them into your hand, and you have slain them in a rage <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11774O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11774O\"></sup><i>which</i> has even reached heaven.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now you are proposing to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11775P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11775P\"></sup>subjugate for yourselves the people of Judah and Jerusalem for male and female slaves. Surely, <i>do</i> you not <i>have</i> transgressions of your own against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God?",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now therefore, listen to me and return the captives <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11776Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11776Q\"></sup>whom you captured from your brothers, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11776R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11776R\"></sup>for the burning anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is against you.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then some of the heads of the sons of Ephraim—Azariah the son of Johanan, Berechiah the son of Meshillemoth, Jehizkiah the son of Shallum, and Amasa the son of Hadlai—arose against those who were coming from the battle,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and said to them, “You must not bring the captives in here, for you are proposing <i>to bring</i> upon us guilt against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> adding to our sins and our guilt; for our guilt is great so that <i>His</i> burning anger is against Israel.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So the armed men left the captives and the spoil before the officers and all the assembly.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11780S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11780S\"></sup>the men who were designated by name arose, took the captives, and they clothed all their naked ones from the spoil; and they gave them clothes and sandals, fed them and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11780T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11780T\"></sup>gave them drink, anointed them <i>with oil</i>, led all their feeble ones on donkeys, and brought them to Jericho, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11780U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11780U\"></sup>the city of palm trees, to their brothers; then they returned to Samaria.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11781V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11781V\"></sup>At that time King Ahaz sent to the kings of Assyria for help.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11782W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11782W\"></sup>For again the Edomites had come and attacked Judah and carried away captives.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11783X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11783X\"></sup>The Philistines also had invaded the cities of the lowland and of the Negev of Judah, and had taken Beth-shemesh, Aijalon, Gederoth, and Soco with its villages, Timnah with its villages, and Gimzo with its villages, and they settled there.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> humbled Judah because of Ahaz king of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11784Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11784Y\"></sup>Israel, for he had brought about a lack of restraint in Judah and was very unfaithful to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11785Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11785Z\"></sup>Tilgath-pilneser king of Assyria came against him and afflicted him instead of strengthening him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11786AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11786AA\"></sup>Although Ahaz took a portion out of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and out of the palace of the king and of the princes, and gave <i>it</i> to the king of Assyria, it did not help him.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Now in the time of his distress this same King Ahaz <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11787AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11787AB\"></sup>became yet more unfaithful to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11788AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11788AC\"></sup>For he sacrificed to the gods of Damascus which had defeated him, and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11788AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11788AD\"></sup>Because the gods of the kings of Aram helped them, I will sacrifice to them that they may help me.” But they became the downfall of him and all Israel.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Moreover, when Ahaz gathered together the utensils of the house of God, he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11789AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11789AE\"></sup>cut the utensils of the house of God in pieces; and he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11789AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11789AF\"></sup>closed the doors of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11789AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11789AG\"></sup>made altars for himself in every corner of Jerusalem.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>In every city of Judah he made high places to burn incense to other gods, and provoked the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of his fathers, to anger.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11791AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11791AH\"></sup>Now the rest of his acts and all his ways, from first to last, behold, they are written in the Book of the Kings of Judah and Israel.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11792AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11792AI\"></sup>So Ahaz slept with his fathers, and they buried him in the city, in Jerusalem, for they did not bring him into the tombs of the kings of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11792AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11792AJ\"></sup>Israel; and Hezekiah his son reigned in his place."
		},
		"29": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">29 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11793A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11793A\"></sup>Hezekiah became king <i>when he was</i> twenty-five years old; and he reigned twenty-nine years in Jerusalem. And his mother’s name <i>was</i> Abijah, the daughter of Zechariah.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11794B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11794B\"></sup>He did right in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, according to all that his father David had done.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>In the first year of his reign, in the first month, he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11795C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11795C\"></sup>opened the doors of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and repaired them.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He brought in the priests and the Levites and gathered them into the square on the east.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then he said to them, “Listen to me, O Levites. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11797D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11797D\"></sup>Consecrate yourselves now, and consecrate the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of your fathers, and carry the uncleanness out from the holy place.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>For our fathers have been unfaithful and have done evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, and have forsaken Him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11798E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11798E\"></sup>turned their faces away from the dwelling place of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and have turned <i>their</i> backs.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They have also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11799F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11799F\"></sup>shut the doors of the porch and put out the lamps, and have not burned incense or offered burnt offerings in the holy place to the God of Israel.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Therefore <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11800G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11800G\"></sup>the wrath of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was against Judah and Jerusalem, and He has made them an object of terror, of horror, and of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11800H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11800H\"></sup>hissing, as you see with your own eyes.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>For behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11801I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11801I\"></sup>our fathers have fallen by the sword, and our sons and our daughters and our wives are in captivity for this.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now it is in my heart <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11802J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11802J\"></sup>to make a covenant with the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel, that His burning anger may turn away from us.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>My sons, do not be negligent now, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11803K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11803K\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has chosen you to stand before Him, to minister to Him, and to be His ministers and burn incense.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then the Levites arose: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11804L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11804L\"></sup>Mahath, the son of Amasai and Joel the son of Azariah, from the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11804M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11804M\"></sup>the Kohathites; and from the sons of Merari, Kish the son of Abdi and Azariah the son of Jehallelel; and from the Gershonites, Joah the son of Zimmah and Eden the son of Joah;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and from the sons of Elizaphan, Shimri and Jeiel; and from the sons of Asaph, Zechariah and Mattaniah;",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and from the sons of Heman, Jehiel and Shimei; and from the sons of Jeduthun, Shemaiah and Uzziel.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>They assembled their brothers, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11807N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11807N\"></sup>consecrated themselves, and went in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11807O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11807O\"></sup>to cleanse the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, according to the commandment of the king <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11807P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11807P\"></sup>by the words of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So the priests went in to the inner part of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to cleanse <i>it</i>, and every unclean thing which they found in the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> they brought out to the court of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Then the Levites received <i>it</i> to carry out to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11808Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11808Q\"></sup>the Kidron valley.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Now they began the consecration <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11809R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11809R\"></sup>on the first <i>day</i> of the first month, and on the eighth day of the month they entered the porch of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Then they consecrated the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in eight days, and finished on the sixteenth day of the first month.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then they went in to King Hezekiah and said, “We have cleansed the whole house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the altar of burnt offering with all of its utensils, and the table of showbread with all of its utensils.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Moreover, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11811S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11811S\"></sup>all the utensils which King Ahaz had discarded during his reign in his unfaithfulness, we have prepared and consecrated; and behold, they are before the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then King Hezekiah arose early and assembled the princes of the city and went up to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>They brought seven bulls, seven rams, seven lambs and seven male goats <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11813T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11813T\"></sup>for a sin offering for the kingdom, the sanctuary, and Judah. And he ordered the priests, the sons of Aaron, to offer <i>them</i> on the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So they slaughtered the bulls, and the priests took the blood and sprinkled it on the altar. They also slaughtered the rams and sprinkled the blood on the altar; they slaughtered the lambs also and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11814U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11814U\"></sup>sprinkled the blood on the altar.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then they brought the male goats of the sin offering before the king and the assembly, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11815V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11815V\"></sup>they laid their hands on them.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The priests slaughtered them and purged the altar with their blood <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11816W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11816W\"></sup>to atone for all Israel, for the king ordered the burnt offering and the sin offering for all Israel.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11817X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11817X\"></sup>He then stationed the Levites in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with cymbals, with harps and with lyres, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11817Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11817Y\"></sup>according to the command of David and of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11817Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11817Z\"></sup>Gad the king’s seer, and of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11817AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11817AA\"></sup>Nathan the prophet; for the command was from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> through His prophets.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The Levites stood with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11818AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11818AB\"></sup>the <i>musical</i> instruments of David, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11818AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11818AC\"></sup>the priests with the trumpets.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then Hezekiah gave the order to offer the burnt offering on the altar. When the burnt offering began, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11819AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11819AD\"></sup>the song to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> also began with the trumpets, <i>accompanied</i> by the instruments of David, king of Israel.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>While the whole assembly worshiped, the singers also sang and the trumpets sounded; all this <i>continued</i> until the burnt offering was finished.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Now at the completion of the burnt offerings, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11821AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11821AE\"></sup>the king and all who were present with him bowed down and worshiped.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Moreover, King Hezekiah and the officials ordered the Levites to sing praises to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with the words of David and Asaph the seer. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11822AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11822AF\"></sup>So they sang praises with joy, and bowed down and worshiped.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then Hezekiah said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11823AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11823AG\"></sup>Now <i>that</i> you have consecrated yourselves to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, come near and bring sacrifices and thank offerings to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.” And the assembly brought sacrifices and thank offerings, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11823AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11823AH\"></sup>all those who were willing <i>brought</i> burnt offerings.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The number of the burnt offerings which the assembly brought was 70 bulls, 100 rams, and 200 lambs; all these were for a burnt offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The consecrated things were 600 bulls and 3,000 sheep.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>But the priests were too few, so that they were unable to skin all the burnt offerings; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11826AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11826AI\"></sup>therefore their brothers the Levites helped them until the work was completed and until the <i>other</i> priests had consecrated themselves. For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11826AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11826AJ\"></sup>the Levites were more conscientious to consecrate themselves than the priests.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>There <i>were</i> also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11827AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11827AK\"></sup>many burnt offerings with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11827AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11827AL\"></sup>the fat of the peace offerings and with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11827AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11827AM\"></sup>the libations for the burnt offerings. Thus the service of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was established <i>again</i>.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Then Hezekiah and all the people rejoiced over what God had prepared for the people, because the thing came about suddenly."
		},
		"30": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">30 </span>Now Hezekiah sent to all Israel and Judah and wrote letters also to Ephraim and Manasseh, that they should come to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at Jerusalem to celebrate the Passover to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>For the king and his princes and all the assembly in Jerusalem had decided <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11830A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11830A\"></sup>to celebrate the Passover in the second month,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>since they could not celebrate it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11831B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11831B\"></sup>at that time, because the priests had not consecrated themselves in sufficient numbers, nor had the people been gathered to Jerusalem.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Thus the thing was right in the sight of the king and all the assembly.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So they established a decree to circulate a proclamation throughout all Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11833C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11833C\"></sup>from Beersheba even to Dan, that they should come to celebrate the Passover to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel at Jerusalem. For they had not celebrated <i>it</i> in great numbers as it was prescribed.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11834D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11834D\"></sup>The couriers went throughout all Israel and Judah with the letters from the hand of the king and his princes, even according to the command of the king, saying, “O sons of Israel, return to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Abraham, Isaac and Israel, that He may return to those of you who escaped <i>and</i> are left from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11834E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11834E\"></sup>the hand of the kings of Assyria.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11835F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11835F\"></sup>Do not be like your fathers and your brothers, who were unfaithful to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of their fathers, so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11835G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11835G\"></sup>He made them a horror, as you see.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now do not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11836H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11836H\"></sup>stiffen your neck like your fathers, but yield to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and enter His sanctuary which He has consecrated forever, and serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11836I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11836I\"></sup>that His burning anger may turn away from you.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11837J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11837J\"></sup>if you return to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, your brothers and your sons <i>will find</i> compassion before those who led them captive and will return to this land. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11837K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11837K\"></sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is gracious and compassionate, and will not turn <i>His</i> face away from you if you return to Him.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So the couriers passed from city to city through the country of Ephraim and Manasseh, and as far as Zebulun, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11838L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11838L\"></sup>they laughed them to scorn and mocked them.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Nevertheless <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11839M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11839M\"></sup>some men of Asher, Manasseh and Zebulun humbled themselves and came to Jerusalem.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11840N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11840N\"></sup>hand of God was also on Judah to give them one heart to do what the king and the princes commanded by the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now many people were gathered at Jerusalem to celebrate the Feast of Unleavened Bread <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11841O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11841O\"></sup>in the second month, a very large assembly.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>They arose and removed the altars which <i>were</i> in Jerusalem; they also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11842P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11842P\"></sup>removed all the incense altars and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11842Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11842Q\"></sup>cast <i>them</i> into the brook Kidron.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11843R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11843R\"></sup>they slaughtered the Passover <i>lambs</i> on the fourteenth of the second month. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11843S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11843S\"></sup>the priests and Levites were ashamed of themselves, and consecrated themselves and brought burnt offerings to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11844T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11844T\"></sup>They stood at their stations after their custom, according to the law of Moses the man of God; the priests sprinkled the blood <i>which they received</i> from the hand of the Levites.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>For <i>there were</i> many in the assembly who had not consecrated themselves; therefore, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11845U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11845U\"></sup>the Levites <i>were</i> over the slaughter of the Passover <i>lambs</i> for everyone who <i>was</i> unclean, in order to consecrate <i>them</i> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>For a multitude of the people, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11846V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11846V\"></sup><i>even</i> many from Ephraim and Manasseh, Issachar and Zebulun, had not purified themselves, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11846W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11846W\"></sup>yet they ate the Passover <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11846X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11846X\"></sup>otherwise than prescribed. For Hezekiah prayed for them, saying, “May the good <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> pardon",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11847Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11847Y\"></sup>everyone who prepares his heart to seek God, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of his fathers, though not according to the purification <i>rules</i> of the sanctuary.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> heard Hezekiah and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11848Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11848Z\"></sup>healed the people.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The sons of Israel present in Jerusalem <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11849AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11849AA\"></sup>celebrated the Feast of Unleavened Bread <i>for</i> seven days with great joy, and the Levites and the priests praised the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> day after day with loud instruments to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then Hezekiah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11850AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11850AB\"></sup>spoke encouragingly to all the Levites who showed good insight <i>in the things</i> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. So they ate for the appointed seven days, sacrificing peace offerings and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11850AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11850AC\"></sup>giving thanks to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of their fathers.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then the whole assembly <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11851AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11851AD\"></sup>decided to celebrate <i>the feast</i> another seven days, so they celebrated the seven days with joy.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11852AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11852AE\"></sup>Hezekiah king of Judah had contributed to the assembly 1,000 bulls and 7,000 sheep, and the princes had contributed to the assembly 1,000 bulls and 10,000 sheep; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11852AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11852AF\"></sup>a large number of priests consecrated themselves.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>All the assembly of Judah rejoiced, with the priests and the Levites and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11853AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11853AG\"></sup>all the assembly that came from Israel, both the sojourners who came from the land of Israel and those living in Judah.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>So there was great joy in Jerusalem, because there was nothing like this in Jerusalem <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11854AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11854AH\"></sup>since the days of Solomon the son of David, king of Israel.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11855AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11855AI\"></sup>the Levitical priests arose and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11855AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11855AJ\"></sup>blessed the people; and their voice was heard and their prayer came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11855AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11855AK\"></sup>His holy dwelling place, to heaven."
		},
		"31": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">31 </span>Now when all this was finished, all Israel who were present went out to the cities of Judah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11856A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11856A\"></sup>broke the pillars in pieces, cut down the Asherim and pulled down the high places and the altars throughout all Judah and Benjamin, as well as in Ephraim and Manasseh, until they had destroyed them all. Then all the sons of Israel returned to their cities, each to his possession.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And Hezekiah appointed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11857B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11857B\"></sup>the divisions of the priests and the Levites by their divisions, each according to his service, <i>both</i> the priests and the Levites, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11857C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11857C\"></sup>for burnt offerings and for peace offerings, to minister and to give thanks and to praise in the gates of the camp of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><i>He</i> also <i>appointed</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11858D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11858D\"></sup>the king’s portion of his goods for the burnt offerings, <i>namely</i>, for the morning and evening burnt offerings, and the burnt offerings for the sabbaths and for the new moons and for the fixed festivals, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11858E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11858E\"></sup>as it is written in the law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Also he commanded the people who lived in Jerusalem to give <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11859F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11859F\"></sup>the portion due to the priests and the Levites, that they might devote themselves to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11859G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11859G\"></sup>the law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>As soon as the order spread, the sons of Israel provided in abundance the first fruits of grain, new wine, oil, honey and of all the produce of the field; and they brought in abundantly <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11860H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11860H\"></sup>the tithe of all.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The sons of Israel and Judah who lived in the cities of Judah also brought in the tithe of oxen and sheep, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11861I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11861I\"></sup>the tithe of sacred gifts which were consecrated to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God, and placed <i>them</i> in heaps.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>In the third month they began to make the heaps, and finished <i>them</i> by the seventh month.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When Hezekiah and the rulers came and saw the heaps, they blessed the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11863J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11863J\"></sup>His people Israel.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then Hezekiah questioned the priests and the Levites concerning the heaps.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Azariah the chief priest <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11865K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11865K\"></sup>of the house of Zadok said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11865L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11865L\"></sup>Since the contributions began to be brought into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, we have had enough to eat with plenty left over, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has blessed His people, and this great quantity is left over.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then Hezekiah commanded <i>them</i> to prepare <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11866M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11866M\"></sup>rooms in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and they prepared <i>them</i>.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>They faithfully brought in the contributions and the tithes and the consecrated things; and Conaniah the Levite <i>was</i> the officer in charge <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11867N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11867N\"></sup>of them and his brother Shimei <i>was</i> second.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Jehiel, Azaziah, Nahath, Asahel, Jerimoth, Jozabad, Eliel, Ismachiah, Mahath and Benaiah <i>were</i> overseers under the authority of Conaniah and Shimei his brother by the appointment of King Hezekiah, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11868O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11868O\"></sup>Azariah <i>was</i> the <i>chief</i> officer of the house of God.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Kore the son of Imnah the Levite, the keeper of the eastern <i>gate, was</i> over the freewill offerings of God, to apportion the contributions for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the most holy things.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Under his authority <i>were</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11870P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11870P\"></sup>Eden, Miniamin, Jeshua, Shemaiah, Amariah and Shecaniah in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11870Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11870Q\"></sup>the cities of the priests, to distribute faithfully <i>their portions</i> to their brothers by divisions, whether great or small,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>without regard to their genealogical enrollment, to the males from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11871R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11871R\"></sup>thirty years old and upward—everyone who entered the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11871S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11871S\"></sup>for his daily obligations—for their work in their duties according to their divisions;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>as well as the priests who were enrolled genealogically according to their fathers’ households, and the Levites <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11872T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11872T\"></sup>from twenty years old and upwards, by their duties <i>and</i> their divisions.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The genealogical enrollment <i>included</i> all their little children, their wives, their sons and their daughters, for the whole assembly, for they consecrated themselves faithfully in holiness.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Also for the sons of Aaron the priests <i>who were</i> in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11874U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11874U\"></sup>the pasture lands of their cities, or in each and every city, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11874V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11874V\"></sup><i>there were</i> men who were designated by name to distribute portions to every male among the priests and to everyone genealogically enrolled among the Levites.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Thus Hezekiah did throughout all Judah; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11875W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11875W\"></sup>he did what <i>was</i> good, right and true before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Every work which he began in the service of the house of God in law and in commandment, seeking his God, he did with all his heart and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11876X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11876X\"></sup>prospered."
		},
		"32": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">32 </span>After these acts of faithfulness <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11877A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11877A\"></sup>Sennacherib king of Assyria came and invaded Judah and besieged the fortified cities, and thought to break into them for himself.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Now when Hezekiah saw that Sennacherib had come and that he intended to make war on Jerusalem,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>he decided with his officers and his warriors to cut off the <i>supply of</i> water from the springs which <i>were</i> outside the city, and they helped him.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So many people assembled <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11880B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11880B\"></sup>and stopped up all the springs and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11880C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11880C\"></sup>the stream which flowed through the region, saying, “Why should the kings of Assyria come and find abundant water?”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And he took courage and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11881D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11881D\"></sup>rebuilt all the wall that had been broken down and erected towers on it, and <i>built</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11881E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11881E\"></sup>another outside wall and strengthened the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11881F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11881F\"></sup>Millo <i>in</i> the city of David, and made weapons and shields in great number.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He appointed military officers over the people and gathered them to him in the square at the city gate, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11882G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11882G\"></sup>spoke encouragingly to them, saying,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11883H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11883H\"></sup>Be strong and courageous, do not fear or be dismayed because of the king of Assyria nor because of all the horde that is with him; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11883I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11883I\"></sup>for the one with us is greater than the one with him.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>With him is <i>only</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11884J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11884J\"></sup>an arm of flesh, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11884K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11884K\"></sup>with us is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God to help us and to fight our battles.” And the people relied on the words of Hezekiah king of Judah.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>After this <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11885L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11885L\"></sup>Sennacherib king of Assyria sent his servants to Jerusalem while he <i>was</i> besieging Lachish with all his forces with him, against Hezekiah king of Judah and against all Judah who <i>were</i> at Jerusalem, saying,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“Thus says Sennacherib king of Assyria, ‘On what are you trusting that you are remaining in Jerusalem under siege?",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Is not Hezekiah misleading you to give yourselves over to die by hunger and by thirst, saying, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God will deliver us from the hand of the king of Assyria”?",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11888M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11888M\"></sup>Has not the same Hezekiah taken away His high places and His altars, and said to Judah and Jerusalem, “You shall worship before one altar, and on it you shall burn incense”?",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Do you not know what I and my fathers have done to all the peoples of the lands? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11889N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11889N\"></sup>Were the gods of the nations of the lands able at all to deliver their land from my hand?",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11890O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11890O\"></sup>Who <i>was there</i> among all the gods of those nations which my fathers utterly destroyed who could deliver his people out of my hand, that your God should be able to deliver you from my hand?",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now therefore, do not let Hezekiah deceive you or mislead you like this, and do not believe him, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11891P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11891P\"></sup>no god of any nation or kingdom was able to deliver his people from my hand or from the hand of my fathers. How much less will your God deliver you from my hand?’”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>His servants spoke further against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God and against His servant Hezekiah.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He also wrote letters to insult the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel, and to speak against Him, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11893Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11893Q\"></sup>As the gods of the nations of the lands have not delivered their people from my hand, so the God of Hezekiah will not deliver His people from my hand.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11894R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11894R\"></sup>They called this out with a loud voice in the language of Judah to the people of Jerusalem who were on the wall, to frighten and terrify them, so that they might take the city.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>They spoke of the God of Jerusalem as of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11895S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11895S\"></sup>the gods of the peoples of the earth, the work of men’s hands.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But King Hezekiah and Isaiah the prophet, the son of Amoz, prayed about this and cried out to heaven.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent an angel who destroyed every mighty warrior, commander and officer in the camp of the king of Assyria. So he returned in shame to his own land. And when he had entered the temple of his god, some of his own children killed him there with the sword.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11898T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11898T\"></sup>saved Hezekiah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem from the hand of Sennacherib the king of Assyria and from the hand of all <i>others</i>, and guided them on every side.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11899U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11899U\"></sup>many were bringing gifts to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at Jerusalem and choice presents to Hezekiah king of Judah, so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11899V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11899V\"></sup>he was exalted in the sight of all nations thereafter.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11900W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11900W\"></sup>In those days Hezekiah became mortally ill; and he prayed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to him and gave him a sign.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>But Hezekiah gave no return for the benefit he received, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11901X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11901X\"></sup>because his heart was proud; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11901Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11901Y\"></sup>therefore wrath came on him and on Judah and Jerusalem.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>However, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11902Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11902Z\"></sup>Hezekiah humbled the pride of his heart, both he and the inhabitants of Jerusalem, so that the wrath of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> did not come on them in the days of Hezekiah.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Now Hezekiah had immense riches and honor; and he made for himself treasuries for silver, gold, precious stones, spices, shields and all kinds of valuable articles,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>storehouses also for the produce of grain, wine and oil, pens for all kinds of cattle and sheepfolds for the flocks.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>He made cities for himself and acquired flocks and herds in abundance, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11905AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11905AA\"></sup>God had given him very great wealth.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>It was Hezekiah who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11906AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11906AB\"></sup>stopped the upper outlet of the waters of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11906AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11906AC\"></sup>Gihon and directed them to the west side of the city of David. And Hezekiah prospered in all that he did.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Even <i>in the matter of</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11907AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11907AD\"></sup>the envoys of the rulers of Babylon, who sent to him to inquire of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11907AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11907AE\"></sup>the wonder that had happened in the land, God left him <i>alone only</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11907AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11907AF\"></sup>to test him, that He might know all that was in his heart.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Hezekiah and his deeds of devotion, behold, they are written in the vision of Isaiah the prophet, the son of Amoz, in the Book of the Kings of Judah and Israel.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>So Hezekiah slept with his fathers, and they buried him in the upper section of the tombs of the sons of David; and all Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11909AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11909AG\"></sup>honored him at his death. And his son Manasseh became king in his place."
		},
		"33": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">33 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11910A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11910A\"></sup>Manasseh was twelve years old when he became king, and he reigned fifty-five years in Jerusalem.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11911B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11911B\"></sup>He did evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> according to the abominations of the nations whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> dispossessed before the sons of Israel.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11912C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11912C\"></sup>he rebuilt the high places which Hezekiah his father had broken down; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11912D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11912D\"></sup>he also erected altars for the Baals and made Asherim, and worshiped all the host of heaven and served them.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11913E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11913E\"></sup>He built altars in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had said, “My name shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11913F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11913F\"></sup>in Jerusalem forever.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>For he built altars for all the host of heaven in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11914G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11914G\"></sup>the two courts of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11915H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11915H\"></sup>He made his sons pass through the fire in the valley of Ben-hinnom; and he practiced witchcraft, used divination, practiced sorcery and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11915I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11915I\"></sup>dealt with mediums and spiritists. He did much evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, provoking Him <i>to anger</i>.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then he put <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11916J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11916J\"></sup>the carved image of the idol which he had made in the house of God, of which God had said to David and to Solomon his son, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11916K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11916K\"></sup>In this house and in Jerusalem, which I have chosen from all the tribes of Israel, I will put My name forever;",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and I will not again remove the foot of Israel from the land <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11917L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11917L\"></sup>which I have appointed for your fathers, if only they will observe to do all that I have commanded them according to all the law, the statutes and the ordinances <i>given</i> through Moses.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Thus Manasseh misled Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem to do more evil than the nations whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> destroyed before the sons of Israel.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Manasseh and his people, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11919M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11919M\"></sup>they paid no attention.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11920N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11920N\"></sup>Therefore the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brought the commanders of the army of the king of Assyria against them, and they captured Manasseh with hooks, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11920O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11920O\"></sup>bound him with bronze <i>chains</i> and took him to Babylon.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11921P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11921P\"></sup>he was in distress, he entreated the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11921Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11921Q\"></sup>humbled himself greatly before the God of his fathers.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>When he prayed to Him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11922R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11922R\"></sup>He was moved by his entreaty and heard his supplication, and brought him again to Jerusalem to his kingdom. Then Manasseh <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11922S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11922S\"></sup>knew that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <i>was</i> God.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Now after this he built the outer wall of the city of David on the west side of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11923T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11923T\"></sup>Gihon, in the valley, even to the entrance of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11923U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11923U\"></sup>Fish Gate; and he encircled the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11923V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11923V\"></sup>Ophel <i>with it</i> and made it very high. Then he put army commanders in all the fortified cities of Judah.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>He also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11924W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11924W\"></sup>removed the foreign gods and the idol from the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as well as all the altars which he had built on the mountain of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and in Jerusalem, and he threw <i>them</i> outside the city.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He set up the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and sacrificed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11925X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11925X\"></sup>peace offerings and thank offerings on it; and he ordered Judah to serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Nevertheless <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11926Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11926Y\"></sup>the people still sacrificed in the high places, <i>although</i> only to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Manasseh even <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11927Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11927Z\"></sup>his prayer to his God, and the words of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11927AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11927AA\"></sup>the seers who spoke to him in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel, behold, they are among the records of the kings of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11927AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11927AB\"></sup>Israel.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>His prayer also and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11928AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11928AC\"></sup><i>how God</i> was entreated by him, and all his sin, his unfaithfulness, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11928AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11928AD\"></sup>the sites on which he built high places and erected the Asherim and the carved images, before he humbled himself, behold, they are written in the records of the Hozai.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So Manasseh slept with his fathers, and they buried him in his own house. And Amon his son became king in his place.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11930AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11930AE\"></sup>Amon <i>was</i> twenty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned two years in Jerusalem.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>He did evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> as Manasseh his father <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11931AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11931AF\"></sup>had done, and Amon sacrificed to all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11931AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11931AG\"></sup>the carved images which his father Manasseh had made, and he served them.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Moreover, he did not humble himself before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11932AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11932AH\"></sup>as his father Manasseh had done, but Amon multiplied guilt.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Finally <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11933AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11933AI\"></sup>his servants conspired against him and put him to death in his own house.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>But the people of the land killed all the conspirators against King Amon, and the people of the land made Josiah his son king in his place."
		},
		"34": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">34 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11935A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11935A\"></sup>Josiah <i>was</i> eight years old when he became king, and he reigned thirty-one years in Jerusalem.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11936B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11936B\"></sup>He did right in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and walked in the ways of his father David and did not turn aside to the right or to the left.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>For in the eighth year of his reign while he was still a youth, he began to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11937C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11937C\"></sup>seek the God of his father David; and in the twelfth year he began <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11937D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11937D\"></sup>to purge Judah and Jerusalem of the high places, the Asherim, the carved images and the molten images.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They tore down the altars of the Baals in his presence, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11938E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11938E\"></sup>the incense altars that were high above them he chopped down; also the Asherim, the carved images and the molten images he broke in pieces and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11938F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11938F\"></sup>ground to powder and scattered <i>it</i> on the graves of those who had sacrificed to them.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11939G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11939G\"></sup>he burned the bones of the priests on their altars and purged Judah and Jerusalem.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11940H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11940H\"></sup>In the cities of Manasseh, Ephraim, Simeon, even as far as Naphtali, in their surrounding ruins,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>he also tore down the altars and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11941I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11941I\"></sup>beat the Asherim and the carved images into powder, and chopped down all the incense altars throughout the land of Israel. Then he returned to Jerusalem.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11942J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11942J\"></sup>Now in the eighteenth year of his reign, when he had purged the land and the house, he sent Shaphan the son of Azaliah, and Maaseiah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11942K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11942K\"></sup>an official of the city, and Joah the son of Joahaz the recorder, to repair the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>They came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11943L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11943L\"></sup>Hilkiah the high priest and delivered the money that was brought into the house of God, which the Levites, the doorkeepers, had collected from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11943M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11943M\"></sup>Manasseh and Ephraim, and from all the remnant of Israel, and from all Judah and Benjamin and the inhabitants of Jerusalem.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then they gave <i>it</i> into the hands of the workmen who had the oversight of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the workmen who were working in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> used it to restore and repair the house.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>They in turn gave <i>it</i> to the carpenters and to the builders to buy quarried stone and timber for couplings and to make beams for the houses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11945N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11945N\"></sup>which the kings of Judah had let go to ruin.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11946O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11946O\"></sup>The men did the work faithfully with foremen over them to supervise: Jahath and Obadiah, the Levites of the sons of Merari, Zechariah and Meshullam of the sons of the Kohathites, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11946P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11946P\"></sup>the Levites, all who were skillful with musical instruments.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><i>They were</i> also over <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11947Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11947Q\"></sup>the burden bearers, and supervised all the workmen from job to job; and <i>some</i> of the Levites <i>were</i> scribes and officials and gatekeepers.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When they were bringing out the money which had been brought into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11948R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11948R\"></sup>Hilkiah the priest found the book of the law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <i>given</i> by Moses.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Hilkiah responded and said to Shaphan the scribe, “I have found the book of the law in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.” And Hilkiah gave the book to Shaphan.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then Shaphan brought the book to the king and reported further word to the king, saying, “Everything that was entrusted to your servants they are doing.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>They have also emptied out the money which was found in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and have delivered it into the hands of the supervisors and the workmen.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Moreover, Shaphan the scribe told the king saying, “Hilkiah the priest gave me a book.” And Shaphan read from it in the presence of the king.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>When the king heard <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11953S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11953S\"></sup>the words of the law, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11953T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11953T\"></sup>he tore his clothes.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then the king commanded Hilkiah, Ahikam the son of Shaphan, Abdon the son of Micah, Shaphan the scribe, and Asaiah the king’s servant, saying,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“Go, inquire of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for me and for those who are left in Israel and in Judah, concerning the words of the book which has been found; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11955U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11955U\"></sup>great is the wrath of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> which is poured out on us because our fathers have not observed the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, to do according to all that is written in this book.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So Hilkiah and <i>those</i> whom the king had told went to Huldah the prophetess, the wife of Shallum the son of Tokhath, the son of Hasrah, the keeper of the wardrobe (now she lived in Jerusalem in the Second Quarter); and they spoke to her regarding this.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>She said to them, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, ‘Tell the man who sent you to Me,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11958V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11958V\"></sup>I am bringing evil on this place and on its inhabitants, <i>even</i> all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11958W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11958W\"></sup>the curses written in the book which they have read in the presence of the king of Judah.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11959X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11959X\"></sup>Because they have forsaken Me and have burned incense to other gods, that they might provoke Me to anger with all the works of their hands; therefore My wrath will be poured out on this place and it shall not be quenched.”’",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But to the king of Judah who sent you to inquire of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, thus you will say to him, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel <i>regarding</i> the words which you have heard,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11961Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11961Y\"></sup>Because your heart was tender and you humbled yourself before God when you heard His words against this place and against its inhabitants, and <i>because</i> you humbled yourself before Me, tore your clothes and wept before Me, I truly have heard you,” declares the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Behold, I will gather you to your fathers and you shall be gathered to your grave in peace, so your eyes will not see all the evil which I will bring on this place and on its inhabitants.”’” And they brought back word to the king.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11963Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11963Z\"></sup>Then the king sent and gathered all the elders of Judah and Jerusalem.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The king went up to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11964AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11964AA\"></sup>all the men of Judah, the inhabitants of Jerusalem, the priests, the Levites and all the people, from the greatest to the least; and he read in their hearing all the words of the book of the covenant which was found in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then the king <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11965AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11965AB\"></sup>stood in his place and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11965AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11965AC\"></sup>made a covenant before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to walk after the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and to keep His commandments and His testimonies and His statutes with all his heart and with all his soul, to perform the words of the covenant written in this book.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Moreover, he made all who were present in Jerusalem and Benjamin to stand <i>with him</i>. So the inhabitants of Jerusalem did according to the covenant of God, the God of their fathers.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Josiah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11967AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11967AD\"></sup>removed all the abominations from all the lands belonging to the sons of Israel, and made all who were present in Israel to serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God. Throughout his lifetime they did not turn from following the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of their fathers."
		},
		"35": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">35 </span>Then Josiah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11968A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11968A\"></sup>celebrated the Passover to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in Jerusalem, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11968B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11968B\"></sup>they slaughtered the Passover <i>animals</i> on the fourteenth <i>day</i> of the first month.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He set the priests in their offices and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11969C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11969C\"></sup>encouraged them in the service of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He also said to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11970D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11970D\"></sup>the Levites who taught all Israel <i>and</i> who were holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “Put the holy ark in the house which Solomon the son of David king of Israel built; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11970E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11970E\"></sup>it will be a burden on <i>your</i> shoulders no longer. Now serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God and His people Israel.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11971F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11971F\"></sup>Prepare <i>yourselves</i> by your fathers’ households in your divisions, according to the writing of David king of Israel and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11971G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11971G\"></sup>according to the writing of his son Solomon.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Moreover, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11972H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11972H\"></sup>stand in the holy place according to the sections of the fathers’ households of your brethren the lay people, and according to the Levites, by division of a father’s household.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11973I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11973I\"></sup>slaughter the Passover <i>animals</i>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11973J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11973J\"></sup>sanctify yourselves and prepare for your brethren to do according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by Moses.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Josiah contributed to the lay people, to all who were present, flocks of lambs and young goats, all for the Passover offerings, numbering 30,000 plus 3,000 bulls; these were from the king’s possessions.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>His officers also contributed a freewill offering to the people, the priests and the Levites. Hilkiah and Zechariah and Jehiel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11975K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11975K\"></sup>the officials of the house of God, gave to the priests for the Passover offerings 2,600 <i>from the flocks</i> and 300 bulls.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11976L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11976L\"></sup>Conaniah also, and Shemaiah and Nethanel, his brothers, and Hashabiah and Jeiel and Jozabad, the officers of the Levites, contributed to the Levites for the Passover offerings 5,000 <i>from the flocks</i> and 500 bulls.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So the service was prepared, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11977M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11977M\"></sup>the priests stood at their stations and the Levites by their divisions according to the king’s command.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11978N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11978N\"></sup>They slaughtered the Passover <i>animals</i>, and while <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11978O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11978O\"></sup>the priests sprinkled the blood <i>received</i> from their hand, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11978P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11978P\"></sup>the Levites skinned <i>them</i>.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then they removed the burnt offerings that <i>they</i> might give them to the sections of the fathers’ households of the lay people to present to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as it is written in the book of Moses. <i>They did</i> this also with the bulls.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11980Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11980Q\"></sup>they roasted the Passover <i>animals</i> on the fire according to the ordinance, and they boiled <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11980R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11980R\"></sup>the holy things in pots, in kettles, in pans, and carried <i>them</i> speedily to all the lay people.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Afterwards they prepared for themselves and for the priests, because the priests, the sons of Aaron, <i>were</i> offering the burnt offerings and the fat until night; therefore the Levites prepared for themselves and for the priests, the sons of Aaron.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The singers, the sons of Asaph, <i>were</i> also at their stations <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11982S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11982S\"></sup>according to the command of David, Asaph, Heman, and Jeduthun the king’s seer; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11982T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11982T\"></sup>the gatekeepers at each gate did not have to depart from their service, because the Levites their brethren prepared for them.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So all the service of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was prepared on that day to celebrate the Passover, and to offer burnt offerings on the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> according to the command of King Josiah.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Thus <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11984U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11984U\"></sup>the sons of Israel who were present celebrated the Passover at that time, and the Feast of Unleavened Bread seven days.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11985V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11985V\"></sup>There had not been celebrated a Passover like it in Israel since the days of Samuel the prophet; nor had any of the kings of Israel celebrated such a Passover as Josiah did with the priests, the Levites, all Judah and Israel who were present, and the inhabitants of Jerusalem.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>In the eighteenth year of Josiah’s reign this Passover was celebrated.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11987W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11987W\"></sup>After all this, when Josiah had set the temple in order, Neco king of Egypt came up to make war at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11987X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11987X\"></sup>Carchemish on the Euphrates, and Josiah went out to engage him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But Neco sent messengers to him, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11988Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11988Y\"></sup>What have we to do with each other, O King of Judah? <i>I am</i> not <i>coming</i> against you today but against the house with which I am at war, and God has ordered me to hurry. Stop for your own sake from <i>interfering with</i> God who is with me, so that He will not destroy you.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>However, Josiah would not turn away from him, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11989Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11989Z\"></sup>disguised himself in order to make war with him; nor did he listen to the words of Neco <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11989AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11989AA\"></sup>from the mouth of God, but came to make war on the plain of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11989AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11989AB\"></sup>Megiddo.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The archers shot King Josiah, and the king said to his servants, “Take me away, for I am badly wounded.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So his servants took him out of the chariot and carried him in the second chariot which he had, and brought him to Jerusalem where he died and was buried in the tombs of his fathers. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11991AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11991AC\"></sup>All Judah and Jerusalem mourned for Josiah.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11992AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11992AD\"></sup>Jeremiah chanted a lament for Josiah. And all the male and female singers speak about Josiah in their lamentations to this day. And they made them an ordinance in Israel; behold, they are also written in the Lamentations.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Josiah and his deeds of devotion as written in the law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and his acts, first to last, behold, they are written in the Book of the Kings of Israel and Judah."
		},
		"36": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">36 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11995A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11995A\"></sup>Then the people of the land took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11995B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11995B\"></sup>Joahaz the son of Josiah, and made him king in place of his father in Jerusalem.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Joahaz was twenty-three years old when he became king, and he reigned three months in Jerusalem.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then the king of Egypt deposed him at Jerusalem, and imposed on the land a fine of one hundred talents of silver and one talent of gold.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The king of Egypt made Eliakim his brother king over Judah and Jerusalem, and changed his name to Jehoiakim. But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11998C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11998C\"></sup>Neco took Joahaz his brother and brought him to Egypt.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11999D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11999D\"></sup>Jehoiakim was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned eleven years in Jerusalem; and he did evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12000E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12000E\"></sup>against him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12000F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12000F\"></sup>bound him with bronze <i>chains</i> to take him to Babylon.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12001G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12001G\"></sup>Nebuchadnezzar also brought <i>some</i> of the articles of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to Babylon and put them in his temple at Babylon.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12002H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12002H\"></sup>Now the rest of the acts of Jehoiakim and the abominations which he did, and what was found against him, behold, they are written in the Book of the Kings of Israel and Judah. And Jehoiachin his son became king in his place.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12003I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12003I\"></sup>Jehoiachin was eight years old when he became king, and he reigned three months and ten days in Jerusalem, and he did evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12004J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12004J\"></sup>At the turn of the year King Nebuchadnezzar sent and brought him to Babylon with the valuable articles of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and he made his kinsman <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12004K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12004K\"></sup>Zedekiah king over Judah and Jerusalem.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12005L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12005L\"></sup>Zedekiah was twenty-one years old when he became king, and he reigned eleven years in Jerusalem.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He did evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12006M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12006M\"></sup>he did not humble himself <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12006N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12006N\"></sup>before Jeremiah the prophet who spoke for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12007O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12007O\"></sup>He also rebelled against King Nebuchadnezzar who had made him swear <i>allegiance</i> by God. But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12007P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12007P\"></sup>he stiffened his neck and hardened his heart against turning to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Furthermore, all the officials of the priests and the people were very unfaithful <i>following</i> all the abominations of the nations; and they defiled the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> which He had sanctified in Jerusalem.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their fathers, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12009Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12009Q\"></sup>sent <i>word</i> to them again and again by His messengers, because He had compassion on His people and on His dwelling place;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>but they <i>continually</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12010R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12010R\"></sup>mocked the messengers of God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12010S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12010S\"></sup>despised His words and scoffed at His prophets, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12010T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12010T\"></sup>until the wrath of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> arose against His people, until there was no remedy.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12011U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12011U\"></sup>Therefore He brought up against them the king of the Chaldeans who slew their young men with the sword in the house of their sanctuary, and had no compassion on young man or virgin, old man or infirm; He gave <i>them</i> all into his hand.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12012V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12012V\"></sup>All the articles of the house of God, great and small, and the treasures of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the treasures of the king and of his officers, he brought <i>them</i> all to Babylon.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12013W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12013W\"></sup>they burned the house of God and broke down the wall of Jerusalem, and burned all its fortified buildings with fire and destroyed all its valuable articles.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Those who had escaped from the sword he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12014X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12014X\"></sup>carried away to Babylon; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12014Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12014Y\"></sup>they were servants to him and to his sons until the rule of the kingdom of Persia,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12015Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12015Z\"></sup>to fulfill the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by the mouth of Jeremiah, until <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12015AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12015AA\"></sup>the land had enjoyed its sabbaths. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12015AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12015AB\"></sup>All the days of its desolation it kept sabbath <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12015AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12015AC\"></sup>until seventy years were complete.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12016AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12016AD\"></sup>Now in the first year of Cyrus king of Persia—in order to fulfill the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12016AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12016AE\"></sup>by the mouth of Jeremiah—the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12016AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12016AF\"></sup>stirred up the spirit of Cyrus king of Persia, so that he sent a proclamation throughout his kingdom, and also <i>put it</i> in writing, saying,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“Thus says Cyrus king of Persia, ‘The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of heaven, has given me all the kingdoms of the earth, and He has appointed me to build Him a house in Jerusalem, which is in Judah. Whoever there is among you of all His people, may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God be with him, and let him go up!’”"
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;